old_content: The line was promoted by the Midland Railway with a view to shortening the distance needed to travel from London to Bradford,{{#tag:ref|The Midland Railway estimated that the distance between London St Pancras and Bradford would be shorter by {{convert|11|mi}}.{{sfn|Batty|1989|p=91}}|name=Distance|group=note}} and also to allow the Midland to make inroads into the Huddersfield, Halifax and Dewsbury areas.{{sfn|Thornhill|1986|p=39}} The proposal received assent from Parliament in 1898, with a estimated cost of £2.1 million.{{sfn|Joy|1984|p=97}} The length of the entire line between Royston and Bradford was listed as {{convert|24|mi}}, and the extension would put Bradford on the main line to London.<ref>{{cite news |title=The Midland Railway in the West Riding |work=The Railway Times |issue=3,118|date=9 October 1897 |page=492|oclc=642446180}}</ref> However, only {{convert|15|mi}} of the proposed length was ever built; {{convert|8|mi}} connecting Royston with Thornhill Junction, {{convert|2.5|mi|0}} connecting to Dewsbury Savile Town, and a {{convert|4.5|mi|adj=on}} branch from Mirfield to Huddersfield Newtown.{{sfn|Joy|1984|pp=260–261, 263}}
new_content: The line was promoted by the Midland Railway with a view to shortening the distance needed to travel from [[St Pancras railway station|London St Pancras]] to Bradford,{{#tag:ref|The Midland Railway estimated that the distance between London St Pancras and Bradford would be shorter by {{convert|11|mi}}.{{sfn|Batty|1989|p=91}}|name=Distance|group=note}} and also to allow the Midland to make inroads into the [[Huddersfield]], [[Halifax, West Yorkshire|Halifax]] and [[Dewsbury]] areas.{{sfn|Thornhill|1986|p=39}} The proposal received assent from Parliament in 1898, with a estimated cost of £2.1 million.{{sfn|Joy|1984|p=97}} The length of the entire line between Royston and Bradford was listed as {{convert|24|mi}}, and the extension would put Bradford on the main line to London.<ref>{{cite news |title=The Midland Railway in the West Riding |work=The Railway Times |issue=3,118|date=9 October 1897 |page=492|oclc=642446180}}</ref> However, only {{convert|15|mi}} of the proposed length was ever built; {{convert|8|mi}} connecting Royston with Thornhill Junction, {{convert|2.5|mi|0}} connecting to Dewsbury Savile Town, and a {{convert|4.5|mi|adj=on}} branch from Mirfield to Huddersfield Newtown.{{sfn|Joy|1984|pp=260–261, 263}}

old_content: There is a widespread false belief that Kennedy made an mistake by saying ''Ich bin '''ein''' Berliner''.  By including the [[indefinite article]] "ein," he supposedly changed the meaning of the sentence from the intended "I am a citizen of Berlin" to "I am a [[Berliner (doughnut)|Berliner]]" (a Berliner being a type of German pastry, similar to a jam- or jelly-filled doughnut), amusing Germans throughout the city. However, this is incorrect from both a grammatical perspective and a historical perspective.
new_content: There is a widespread false belief that Kennedy made a mistake by saying ''Ich bin '''ein''' Berliner''. By including the [[indefinite article]] "ein," he supposedly changed the meaning of the sentence from the intended "I am a citizen of Berlin" to "I am a [[Berliner (doughnut)|Berliner]]" (a Berliner being a type of German pastry, similar to a jam- or jelly-filled doughnut), amusing Germans throughout the city. However, this is incorrect from both a grammatical perspective and a historical perspective.

old_content: In April 2018, United States Senator [[John McCain]] sent Kara-Murza a message revealing that he, McCain, had been diagnosed with brain cancer and requesting that Kara-Murza, who had worked with McCain on issues relating to Russia since 2010, serve as a pallbearer at the senator's eventual funeral. Kara-Murza later said that he was "speechless", "heartbroken", and "close to tears", and that doing so would be "the most heartbreaking honor that anyone could think of". McCain died on 25 August; Kara-Murza joined fourteen others chosen by McCain himself, including the then former Vice President [[Joe Biden]] and actor [[Warren Beatty]], as a pallbearer at McCain's funeral at the [[Washington National Cathedral]] on 1 September. McCain's choice of Kara-Murza was described by ''[[Politico]]'' as a "final dig" at Putin, of whom McCain was a vocal critic, and at U.S. President [[Donald Trump]], for his apparent closeness to the Russian president.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Meyer|first=Josh|url=https://www.politico.com/story/2018/08/28/john-mccain-pallbearer-russia-799061|title=McCain's choice of Russian dissident as pallbearer is final dig at Putin, Trump|work=[[Politico]]|date=28 August 2018|access-date=29 August 2018|archive-date=6 June 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200606115648/https://www.politico.com/story/2018/08/28/john-mccain-pallbearer-russia-799061|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Zurcher|first=Anthony|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-45363080|title=Why McCain picked these 15 pallbearers|work=[[BBC News]]|access-date=1 September 2018|date=31 August 2018|archive-date=1 September 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180901021045/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-45363080|url-status=live}}</ref>

old_content: The [[Lagos]] chamber of commerce and industry pioneered the establishment of the chamber movement in [[Nigeria]] with its establishment in 1888 when Nigeria was still under [[British]] coloniel rule. The chamber movement was however slow during the era of independence in 1960. NACCIMA was incorporated in April 1960 as association of Chambers of commerce in [[Nigeria]] and the Southern Cameroons. In April 1963 it was re-named to Association of Chambers of commerce and mines of Nigeria. In 1972, it agreed to change its name to Nigerian Association Of Chambers Of Commerce, Industry, Mines And Agriculture. NACCIMA'S membership and the chamber movement in Nigeria as a whole experienced a rapid trajectory between 1978 and 2021 with a boost in the membership in all the 36 states.<ref>{{Cite web|date=2024-03-26|title=naccima boss confident trade investment minister drive real sector growth|url=https://www.premiumtimesng.com/business-news/681016-naccima-speaks-on-cbn-forex-backlog.html/|access-date=2024-03-26|website=premiumtimesng.com|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=2024-04-01|title=naccima plans stakeholders consultation over bank recapitalisation|url=https://punching.com/naccima-plans-stakeholders-consultation-over-bank-recapitalisation/%3famp/|access-date=2024-04-01|website=punchng.com|language=en-US}}</ref>

The chamber movement was however slow during the era of independence in 1960. NACCIMA was incorporated in April 1960 as association of Chambers of commerce in [[Nigeria]] and the Southern Cameroons. In April 1963 it was re-named to Association of Chambers of commerce and mines of Nigeria. In 1972, it agreed to change its name to Nigerian Association Of Chambers Of Commerce, Industry, Mines And Agriculture. NACCIMA'S membership and the chamber movement in Nigeria as a whole experienced a rapid trajectory between 1978 and 2021 with a boost in the membership in all the 36 states.<ref>{{Cite web|date=2024-03-26|title=naccima boss confident trade investment minister drive real sector growth|url=https://www.premiumtimesng.com/business-news/681016-naccima-speaks-on-cbn-forex-backlog.html/|access-date=2024-03-26|website=premiumtimesng.com|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=2024-04-01|title=naccima plans stakeholders consultation over bank recapitalisation|url=https://punching.com/naccima-plans-stakeholders-consultation-over-bank-recapitalisation/%3famp/|access-date=2024-04-01|website=punchng.com|language=en-US}}</ref>

old_content: In an interview with ''[[Afropop Worldwide]]'' on 10 July 2019, Ipupa announced that his sixth studio album, ''Tokooos II'', was nearing completion.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Greenstreet |first=Morgan |date=10 July 2019 |title=Interview with Fally Ipupa |url=https://afropop.org/client-uploads/pdf/Fally-French-Int-2019.pdf |access-date=17 October 2023 |website=Afropop.org |page=3 |language=fr}}</ref> He later promoted the album with a concert at the Accor Arena in Paris on 28 February 2020.<ref>{{Cite web |date=28 February 2020 |title=Musique : Fally Ipupa en concert ce vendredi à Paris |url=https://www.radiookapi.net/2020/02/28/actualite/culture/musique-fally-ipupa-en-concert-ce-vendredi-paris |access-date=17 October 2023 |website=Radio Okapi |language=fr}}</ref> ''Tokooos II'' was released on 18 December 2020 by Elektra France. The digital edition contained 16 songs and the physical edition 22.<ref name=":5">{{Cite web |last=Okokana |first=Bruno |date=12 December 2020 |title=Musique : Fally Ipupa lance "Tokoos II" |trans-title=Music: Fally Ipupa launches "Tokoos II" |url=https://www.adiac-congo.com/content/musique-fally-ipupa-lance-tokoos-ii-122500 |access-date=17 October 2023 |website=www.adiac-congo.com |language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=23 November 2020 |title=RDC-Musique : l'album Tokooos II de Fally Ipupa sort le 18 décembre |url=https://actualite.cd/2020/11/23/rdc-musique-lalbum-tokooos-ii-de-fally-ipupa-sort-le-18-decembre |access-date=17 October 2023 |website=Actualite.cd |language=fr}}</ref> The album features collaborations with [[Dadju]], Naza, [[Ninho]], and [[M. Pokora]] and fuses traditional Congolese rumba, soukous, ndombolo, R&B, and [[Trap music|trap beats]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Rédaction |first=La |date=24 November 2020 |title=Dans Tokooos 2, Fally Ipupa fait appel à Matt Pokora, Dadju, Naza et bien d'autres artistes ! |url=https://www.strong2kinmoov.com/2020/11/dans-tokooos-2-fally-ipupa-fait-appel-a-matt-pokora-dadju-naza-et-bien-dautres-artistes/ |access-date=27 February 2022 |website=Strong2kin Moov |language=fr-FR}}</ref><ref name=":5" /> Reviewing for ''Pan African Music'', Rémi Benchebra described the album as being "guided by love, a theme dear to rumbists", and "a voice which combines fragility with power".<ref name=":12">{{Cite web |last=Benchebra |first=Rémi |date=23 December 2020 |title=Tokooos II: l'aigle du Congo, Fally Ipupa, vole encore plus haut |url=https://pan-african-music.com/tokooos-ii-laigle-du-congo-fally-ipupa-vole-encore-plus-haut/ |access-date=1 August 2023 |website=PAM {{!}} Pan African Music |language=fr-FR}}</ref> On 26 December 2020, Ipupa sold out [[:fr:Hôtel Ivoire|Sofitel Abidjan Hôtel Ivoire]] in Ivory Coast and received the Best African Artist of the Year prize at the fourth edition of the African Talents Awards.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Mpiutu |first=Miguel Jegou |date=26 December 2020 |title=Côte d'ivoire : Fally Ipupa vend tous les billets pour son concert au Sofitel Abidjan Hôtel |trans-title=Ivory Coast: Fally Ipupa sells all tickets for his concert at the Sofitel Abidjan Hotel |url=https://mbote.cd/celebrites/cote-divoire-fally-ipupa-vend-tous-les-billets-pour-son-concert-au-sofitel-abidjan-hotel/57601/ |access-date=17 October 2023 |website=Mbote |language=fr-FR |publication-place=Kinshasa, Democratic Republic of the Congo}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Masela |first=Nioni |date=29 December 2020 |title=Afrique : African Talents Awards – Fally Ipupa sacré meilleur artiste africain de l'année |language=fr |trans-title=Africa: African Talents Awards – Fally Ipupa crowned African artist of the year |work=AllAfrica |url=https://fr.allafrica.com/stories/202012290682.html |access-date=17 October 2023}}</ref> In February 2021, he performed at the [[Yaoundé Multipurpose Sports Complex]] in Cameroon in front of 3,000 people, in celebration of president [[Paul Biya]]'s 88th birthday.<ref>{{Cite news |date=15 February 2021 |title=Cameroun : Spectacle – Fally met le feu |language=fr |trans-title=Cameroon: Show – Fally sets fire |work=AllAfrica |url=https://fr.allafrica.com/stories/202102150776.html |access-date=18 October 2023}}</ref> To promote the album further, he unveiled a lineup of multiple African concerts, referred to as the "Tokoos II Tour Part I"<ref name=":27">{{Cite news |last=Yunduka |first=Karim |date=7 October 2021 |title=Congo-Brazzaville : "Tokoos ll" – La tournée africaine de Fally Ipupa débute ce 9 octobre |language=fr |trans-title=Congo-Brazzaville: "Tokoos ll" – Fally Ipupa's African tour begins October 9 |work=AllAfrica |url=https://fr.allafrica.com/stories/202110080459.html |access-date=18 October 2023}}</ref> The tour kicked off on 9 October in [[Dar es Salaam]], Tanzania, and concluded on 10 January 2022, in [[Bafoussam]], Cameroon. It covered 19 countries, primarily in [[African French|French-speaking regions]], where he performed with his accompanying group F'Victeam.<ref name=":27" />

The digital edition contained 16 songs and the physical edition 22.<ref name=":5">{{Cite web |last=Okokana |first=Bruno |date=12 December 2020 |title=Musique : Fally Ipupa lance "Tokoos II" |trans-title=Music: Fally Ipupa launches "Tokoos II" |url=https://www.adiac-congo.com/content/musique-fally-ipupa-lance-tokoos-ii-122500 |access-date=17 October 2023 |website=www.adiac-congo.com |language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=23 November 2020 |title=RDC-Musique : l'album Tokooos II de Fally Ipupa sort le 18 décembre |url=https://actualite.cd/2020/11/23/rdc-musique-lalbum-tokooos-ii-de-fally-ipupa-sort-le-18-decembre |access-date=17 October 2023 |website=Actualite.cd |language=fr}}</ref> The album features collaborations with [[Dadju]], Naza, [[Ninho]], and [[M. Pokora]] and fuses traditional Congolese rumba, soukous, ndombolo, R&B, and [[Trap music|trap beats]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Rédaction |first=La |date=24 November 2020 |title=Dans Tokooos 2, Fally Ipupa fait appel à Matt Pokora, Dadju, Naza et bien d'autres artistes ! |url=https://www.strong2kinmoov.com/2020/11/dans-tokooos-2-fally-ipupa-fait-appel-a-matt-pokora-dadju-naza-et-bien-dautres-artistes/ |access-date=27 February 2022 |website=Strong2kin Moov |language=fr-FR}}</ref><ref name=":5" /> Reviewing for ''Pan African Music'', Rémi Benchebra described the album as being "guided by love, a theme dear to rumbists", and "a voice which combines fragility with power".<ref name=":12">{{Cite web |last=Benchebra |first=Rémi |date=23 December 2020 |title=Tokooos II: l'aigle du Congo, Fally Ipupa, vole encore plus haut |url=https://pan-african-music.com/tokooos-ii-laigle-du-congo-fally-ipupa-vole-encore-plus-haut/ |access-date=1 August 2023 |website=PAM {{!}} Pan African Music |language=fr-FR}}</ref> On 26 December 2020, Ipupa sold out [[:fr:Hôtel Ivoire|Sofitel Abidjan Hôtel Ivoire]] in Ivory Coast and received the Best African Artist of the Year prize at the fourth edition of the African Talents Awards.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Mpiutu |first=Miguel Jegou |date=26 December 2020 |title=Côte d'ivoire : Fally Ipupa vend tous les billets pour son concert au Sofitel Abidjan Hôtel |trans-title=Ivory Coast: Fally Ipupa sells all tickets for his concert at the Sofitel Abidjan Hotel |url=https://mbote.cd/celebrites/cote-divoire-fally-ipupa-vend-tous-les-billets-pour-son-concert-au-sofitel-abidjan-hotel/57601/ |access-date=17 October 2023 |website=Mbote |language=fr-FR |publication-place=Kinshasa, Democratic Republic of the Congo}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Masela |first=Nioni |date=29 December 2020 |title=Afrique : African Talents Awards – Fally Ipupa sacré meilleur artiste africain de l'année |language=fr |trans-title=Africa: African Talents Awards – Fally Ipupa crowned African artist of the year |work=AllAfrica |url=https://fr.allafrica.com/stories/202012290682.html |access-date=17 October 2023}}</ref> In February 2021, he performed at the [[Yaoundé Multipurpose Sports Complex]] in Cameroon in front of 3,000 people, in celebration of president [[Paul Biya]]'s 88th birthday.<ref>{{Cite news |date=15 February 2021 |title=Cameroun : Spectacle – Fally met le feu |language=fr |trans-title=Cameroon: Show – Fally sets fire |work=AllAfrica |url=https://fr.allafrica.com/stories/202102150776.html |access-date=18 October 2023}}</ref> To promote the album further, he unveiled a lineup of multiple African Ipupa débute ce 9 octobre |language=fr |trans-title=Congo-Brazzaville: "Tokoos ll" – Fally Ipupa's African tour begins October 9 |work=AllAfrica |url=https://fr.allafrica.com/stories/202110080459.html old_content: Coal is a type of [[fossil fuel]], formed when dead [[plant matter]] decays into [[peat]] and is converted into coal by the heat and pressure of deep burial over millions of years.<ref name="EIA Coal Explained">{{cite web | url=https://www.eia.gov/energyexplained/index.cfm?page=coal_home | title=Coal Explained | publisher=[[US Energy Information Administration]] | work=Energy Explained | date=21 April 2017 | access-date=13 November 2017 | url-status=live | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171208115825/https://www.eia.gov/energyexplained/index.cfm?page=coal_home | archive-date=8 December 2017}}</ref> Vast deposits of coal originate in former [[wetland]]s called [[coal forest]]s that covered much of the Earth's tropical land areas during the late [[Carboniferous]] ([[Pennsylvanian (geology)|Pennsylvanian]]) and [[Permian]] times.<ref name=ClealThomas2005>{{cite journal | last1 = Cleal | first1 = C. J. | last2 = Thomas | first2 = B. old_content: '''''The Chase''''' is a 1994 American [[action film|action comedy film]] directed by [[Adam Rifkin]] and starring [[Charlie Sheen]] and [[Kristy Swanson]]. Set in [[California]], the film follows a wrongfully convicted man who kidnaps a wealthy heiress and leads police on a lengthy [[car chase]] in an attempt to escape prison, while the news media dramatize the chase to absurd extents. It features [[Henry Rollins]], [[Josh Mostel]], and [[Ray Wise]] in supporting roles, with [[cameo appearance]]s by [[Anthony Kiedis]] and [[Flea (musician)|Flea]] of the rock band [[Red Hot Chili Peppers]].

old_content: The Royston to Thornhill line was a Midland Railway venture constructed in West Yorkshire, England, that had the intent to allow trains to travel from Sheffield to Bradford without going through Leeds. The scheme, which was promoted as the West Riding Lines, would have travelled underneath Bradford City Centre in a long tunnel and ended up in the Aire Valley providing a [[Bradford Crossrail|through line]] across Bradford. In the event, only the section from Royston to Thornhill, a smaller branch to a goods station at Dewsbury Savile Town, and a longer branch from Mirfield to Huddersfield were ever built. By the late 1960s, the line had all been closed, however, the 21-arch viaduct at Crigglestone still remains.
new_content: The Royston to Thornhill line was a [[Midland Railway]] venture constructed in [[West Yorkshire]], England, that had the intent to allow trains to travel from [[Sheffield Midland railway station|Sheffield]] to [[Bradford Exchange railway station|Bradford]] without going through {{rws|Leeds}}. The scheme, which was promoted as the West Riding Lines, would have travelled underneath Bradford city centre in a long tunnel and ended up in the [[Airedale|Aire Valley]] providing a [[Bradford Crossrail|through line]] across Bradford. In the event, only the section from Royston to Thornhill, a smaller branch to a goods station at Dewsbury Savile Town, and a longer branch from Mirfield to Huddersfield were ever built. By the late 1960s, the lines had all been closed, however, the viaducts at Bradley, Crigglestone, and Horbury still remain.

old_content: Laurie Ann Powell Compton, 18, a [[Gloucester High School (Virginia)|Gloucester High School]] graduate, went missing on March 8, 1988, after having an argument with her boyfriend which ended with Laurie getting out of his car. She was last seen by him at 23:30 p.m. walking on the “dark and deserted” Route 614 towards Route 17 in the White Marsh area in Gloucester County. She was wearing a purple pullover, cotton shirt with a white collar, purple and cream coloured pants, and a dungaree jacket. Laurie was not scheduled to be at work on March 9 and her family assumed she was staying with a friend. When she did not turn up for work on March 10 her stepfather reported her missing. On Saturday April 2, 1988, Laurie’s body was spotted floating in the [[James River (Virginia)|James River]] off Craney Island near Ragged Island. Her body was found nude, no bindings, and with multiple stab wounds to her back. Her death certificate stated ‘unknown’ for date and place of injury. Compton worked for the same security company where Pettinger and Edwards' mother worked at the time of her murder.

old_content: An Evolutionary Tale of Sexual Survival | publisher = Springer US |year = 2013|page=99|isbn= 978-1-48995-988-1 |url= https://books.google.com/books?id=dnf1BwAAQBAJ&pg=PA99}}</ref> The [[Hemipenis#Hemiclitoris|hemiclitoris]] is one-half of a paired structure in [[squamates]] ([[lizard]]s and [[snake]]s). Some [[Intersex (biology)|intersex]] female bears mate and give birth through the tip of the clitoris; these species are [[grizzly bear]]s, [[brown bear]]s, [[American black bear]]s and [[polar bear]]s. Although the bears have been described as having "a birth canal that runs through the clitoris rather than forming a separate vagina" (a feature that is estimated to make up 10 to 20 percent of the bears' population),<ref name="Girshick_Roughgarden" /> scientists state that female [[spotted hyena]]s are the only non-intersex female mammals devoid of an external vaginal opening, and whose sexual anatomy is distinct from usual intersex cases.<ref name="Glickman" />

old_content: The parents of a [[stillbirth|stillborn]] fetus sued for wrongful death, and the trial court dismissed the complaint on the grounds that there was no such cause of action.  The Supreme Court of Ohio held that a cause of action would lie.  The court recognized several statutory indicators that a stillborn fetus might properly be considered a decedent, including clauses in the [[Uniform Anatomical Gift Act]] and the [[rule against perpetuities]].  The court also recognized the arbitrariness of allowing recovery for wrongful death caused by negligently inflicted prenatal injuries in the case where the death occurs shortly after a live birth and disallowing recovering when the death occurred shortly before birth.  The court held that the wrongful death action would only lie for a viable fetus that was carried full term.<ref>Henderson, et al., p. 332</ref>
new_content: The parents of a [[stillbirth|stillborn]] fetus sued for wrongful death, and the trial court dismissed the complaint on the grounds that there was no such cause of action.  The Supreme Court of Ohio held that a cause of action would lie.  The court recognized several [[statutory]] indicators that a stillborn fetus might properly be considered a decedent, including clauses in the [[Uniform Anatomical Gift Act]] and the [[rule against perpetuities]].  The court also recognized the arbitrariness of allowing recovery for wrongful death caused by negligently inflicted prenatal injuries in the case where the death occurs shortly after a live birth and disallowing recovering when the death occurred shortly before birth.  The court held that the wrongful death action would only lie for a viable fetus that was carried full term.<ref>Henderson, et al., p. 332</ref>

old_content: '''Fort Pontchartrain du Détroit''' or '''Fort Detroit''' (1701–1796) was a [[fortification]] established in 1701 on the north side of the [[Detroit River]] by French trader and military officer [[Antoine de la Mothe Cadillac]]. A French colony based on the [[North American fur trade|fur trade]], missionary work and farming developed in the area near the fort. The site is located in what is now downtown [[Detroit]], northeast of the intersection of Washington Boulevard and West Jefferson Avenue.
new_content: '''Fort Pontchartrain du Détroit''' or '''Fort Detroit''' (1701–1796) was a French and later British [[fortification]] established in 1701 on the north side of the [[Detroit River]] by [[Antoine de la Mothe Cadillac]]. A colony based on the [[North American fur trade|fur trade]], farming and missionary work developed in the area near the fort. The site is located in what is now downtown [[Detroit]], northeast of the intersection of Washington Boulevard and West Jefferson Avenue.

old_content: The stadium's outfield, drainage and pitch construction is being overseen by LandTek Group—a company that has worked on playing surfaces for New York's [[Citi Field]] and [[Yankee Stadium]], and various [[NFL]] stadiums. The outfield will use [[Kentucky bluegrass]], and the [[Cricket pitch#Drop-in pitches|drop-in pitch]] will use Tahoma [[bermudagrass]] surfaces prepared in Florida in consultation with the [[Adelaide Oval]]'s head groundskeeper Damian Hough. The pitches posed particular challenges due to the limited timeframe, and the logstical aspects of the construction process; six of the ten trays needed to be shipped from Adelaide, the grass had to be grown in Florida's warmer climate due to New York's cold winter, and the pitches will have to be transported by [[Semi-trailer truck|semi-trailers]] with blankets to protect the grass and soil from wind and the different climate conditions along the [[East Coast of the United States|East Coast]]. Hough noted that "I've never moved a pitch further than from Adelaide Oval to [[Karen Rolton Oval]], so moving them for two days on a fleet of semi-trailers certainly throws up a few different issues."<ref>{{Cite web |last=Ramsey |first=Andrew |date=2024-04-10 |title=Inside Adelaide's pioneering role in New York's World Cup pitch |url=https://www.cricket.com.au/news/3961231/adelaide-oval-damian-hough-role-new-york-t20-world-cup-nassau-county-cricket-stadium-eisenhower-park-india-pakistan |access-date=2024-04-14 |website=Cricket.com.au |publisher=[[Cricket Australia]] |language=en}}</ref><ref name=":1" />
new_content: The stadium's outfield, drainage and pitch construction is being overseen by The LandTek Group—a company that has worked on playing surfaces for New York's [[Citi Field]] and [[Yankee Stadium]], and various [[NFL]] stadiums. The outfield will use [[Kentucky bluegrass]], and the [[Cricket pitch#Drop-in pitches|drop-in pitch]] will use Tahoma [[bermudagrass]] surfaces prepared in Florida at LTG Sports Turf One, in consultation with the [[Adelaide Oval]]'s head groundskeeper Damian Hough. The pitches posed particular challenges due to the limited timeframe, and the logstical aspects of the construction process; six of the ten trays needed to be shipped from Adelaide, the grass had to be grown in Florida's warmer climate due to New York's cold winter, and the pitches will have to be transported by [[Semi-trailer truck|semi-trailers]] with blankets to protect the grass and soil from wind and the different climate conditions along the [[East Coast of the United States|East Coast]]. Hough noted that "I've never moved a pitch further than from Adelaide Oval to [[Karen Rolton Oval]], so moving them for two days on a fleet of semi-trailers certainly throws up a few different issues."<ref>{{Cite web |last=Ramsey |first=Andrew |date=2024-04-10 |title=Inside Adelaide's pioneering role in New York's World Cup pitch |url=https://www.cricket.com.au/news/3961231/adelaide-oval-damian-hough-role-new-york-t20-world-cup-nassau-county-cricket-stadium-eisenhower-park-india-pakistan |access-date=2024-04-14 |website=Cricket.com.au |publisher=[[Cricket Australia]] |language=en}}</ref><ref name=":1" />

old_content: The Eastend Area is rich in history and geology, and is rife with paleontological sites. A Métis settlement developed north of Eastend, and in the 1870s a [[Hudson’s Bay Company]] trading post was established in the region. In the mid 1880s as bison populations were being decimated on the eastern plains, the area became an important hunting ground that nearby First Nations tribes regularly fought over. The post only lasted one season, due to hostilities between the neighbouring tribes. Many years later, this site became known as Chimney Coulee – the name being derived from the remnants of stone chimneys that were once a part of Métis homes.
new_content: The Eastend Area is rich in history and geology, and is rife with paleontological sites. The post only lasted one season, due to hostilities between the neighbouring tribes. Many years later, this site became known as Chimney Coulee – the name being derived from the remnants of stone chimneys that were once a part of Métis homes.

old_content: The combination of open world and sandbox mechanics can lead towards [[emergent gameplay]], complex reactions that emerge (either expectedly or unexpectedly) from the interaction of relatively simple game mechanics.<ref>{{Cite web | title = Le Gameplay emergent|language=fr | work = jeuxvideo.com |date=January 19, 2006 | url = http://www.jeuxvideo.com/dossiers/00006203/le-gameplay-emergent.htm}}</ref> According to [[Peter Molyneux]], emergent gameplay appears wherever a game has a good [[simulation]] system that allows players to play in the world and have it respond realistically to their actions. It is what made ''[[SimCity]]'' and ''[[The Sims]]'' compelling to players. Similarly, being able to freely interact with the city's inhabitants in ''[[Grand Theft Auto]]'' added an extra dimension to the series.<ref name="moly_spy">{{cite news|last=Kosak |first=Dave |title=The Future of Games from a Design Perspective |publisher=gamespy.com |date=March 7, 2004 |url=http://archive.gamespy.com/articles/march04/dice/molyneux/index.shtml |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090114164207/http://archive.gamespy.com/articles/march04/dice/molyneux/index.shtml |archive-date=January 14, 2009}}</ref>

old_content: In December 2004, it was announced that a unit would be formalised for this role as part of the wider [[Delivering Security in a Changing World|future army structure]]. It was initially conceived as a [[battalion]] of "Rangers", similar to the [[75th Ranger Regiment|United States Army Rangers]].<ref name=Telegraph2005>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/1488020/Britain-to-double-commitment-to-the-war-on-terror-with-SAS-Lite.html|title=Britain to double commitment to the war on terror with 'SAS Lite'|newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|date=17 April 2005 |access-date=12 January 2017}}</ref> The SFSG's formation was announced officially by the then [[Secretary of State for Defence]] [[John Reid, Baron Reid of Cardowan|John Reid]] in [[Parliament of the United Kingdom|Parliament]] on 20 April 2006.<ref name=hansard>{{Cite web|access-date=26 March 2010|publisher=[[Parliament of the United Kingdom]]|title=Special Forces Support Group|url=https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200506/cmhansrd/vo060420/wmstext/60420m01.htm}}</ref> It was established to support British special forces units in battle overseas and on domestic "[[counter-terrorist]]" operations.<ref name="mod" /> The unit comprises a [[battalion]] of [[Parachute Regiment (United Kingdom)|Parachute Regiment]] soldiers, a [[Company_(military_unit)|company]] of [[Royal Marine]] commandos, and a small platoon of [[RAF Regiment]] gunners. old_content: [[Language]] is an important element in human culture. It is the primary abstract artifact by which culture is transmitted extragenetically (fulfilling points 3 and 4). Only so few can be shown, much more must be explained. Most transmission of the knowledge, ideas, and values that make up a given culture, from the ten commandments to this entry, is done through language. Again, language is an aspect from which humans differ from other animals in degree rather than kind. Once more it is other apes who share the greatest similarities with humans. Though these primates lack the [[larynx]] structure that allows for sophisticated vocalization, there are other ways of communicating. The famous female [[gorilla]], [[Koko the gorilla|Koko]], was taught to communicate in [[American sign language]], and she taught it to other gorillas as well. Also, this computing class is pretty boring because we have to do a PBA

old_content: ''Paruthiveeran'' was entirely shot in [[Madurai]] and its surroundings.<ref name="hindu.com">{{cite news| url=http://www.hindu.com/2007/02/13/stories/2007021318030200.htm | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070226225134/http://www.hindu.com/2007/02/13/stories/2007021318030200.htm | url-status=dead | archive-date=26 February 2007 | location=Chennai, India | work=[[The Hindu]] | title=Behind the scenes of "Paruthiveeran" | date=13 February 2007}}</ref> After two years of making, the film was released on 23 February 2007 and received universal critical acclaim. The female lead of this film [[Priyamani]] has won the [[National Film Award for Best Actress]] (2006) for her brilliant and intense performance as a gang rape victim. In this film [[Priyamani]]'s voice modulation and the dialogue delivery in Madurai Tamil accent is considered as the finest performance output given by an actress in the Tamil film industry till date. The film won prizes at major film award ceremonies in India, including two [[National Film Awards]], six [[Filmfare Awards South]] and two [[Tamil Nadu State Film Awards]], among others, whilst being screened at several international film festivals such as the [[Berlin International Film Festival]] and the [[Osian's Cinefan Festival of Asian and Arab Cinema]] as well. It also emerged a huge commercial success, running successfully for more than one year in theatres.<ref name="'Paruthi Veeran' 450 not out!">{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/36564.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080215071858/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/36564.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=15 February 2008|title='Paruthi Veeran' 450 not out!|website=IndiaGlitz.com|access-date=21 July 2009}}</ref>

old_content: As tagged since November 2021, thus article contains [[WP:original research]]. In particular, the "provided taxonomical classification" (see previous post) does not correspond to any reliably published classification. Moreover this classification content many blatant errors and, very often gives much more emphasis on marginal concepts than on fundamental concepts. In particular, the section "Concepts" lists three items: [[mathematical object]], which is not a topic in mathematics, but only a jargon term; [[mathematical structure]]; and [[abstraction]], which is not really a mathematical process. On the other hand, [[theorem]]s and [[proof (mathematics)|proof]]s are not mentioned, although most mathematicians consider that something is mathematics only if theorems and proofs are implied. So, for a taxonomy, as well for the other purposes cited above, [[:Category:Mathematics]] is much more accurate and useful.

old_content: In 2002, Woolfalk began teaching as a Teaching Artist for the nonprofit [[Publicolor]] in New York City. She then teached at Architreasures and the [[School of the Art Institute of Chicago]] the following year. In 2006, Woolfalk became a thesis advisor at the [[Minneapolis College of Art and Design]]. In 2007 she worked as a mentor at the [[New York Foundation for the Arts]] in New York City. Woolfalk was also a visiting artist at the [[University at Buffalo|University of Buffalo]] in 2009 and the [[University of Hartford]] in 2010, respectively. In 2012, she became a graduate advisor at the [[School of the Art Institute of Chicago|Art Institute of Chicago]] and a BFA critic at [[Parsons School of Design]]. She was a visiting artist at [[Montclair State University]]. She stayed a visiting artist at Montclair State University in 2013 and became an adjunct professor at Parsons School of Design where she held the adjunct professor position until 2018.<ref name=oldcv>{{Cite web|last=Woolfalk|first=Saya|title=Teaching and Mentoring Experience|url=https://static1.squarespace.com/static/574ef83b4d088e84c523b0e8/t/5c5cb3a16e9a7f7a0c7dd28f/1549579206130/Teaching-SayaWoolfalk.pdf}}</ref>

old_content: On September 22, 2021, Titan Comics released under the Hard Case Crime imprint ''Gun Honey'' #1, Ardai's first written work for the comics medium. The book, which is drawn by Ang Hor Kheng, and features covers by [[Bill Sienkiewicz]], [[Robert McGinnis]], and [[Adam Hughes]], centers upon weapons smuggler Joanna Tan, who after helping a convict out of prison, is chosen by the U.S. government to track him down and return him.<ref name=CBR8.6.21/> The four-issue miniseries was conceived by Ardai when he conceived of Hard Case Crime Comics five years prior,<ref name=CBR6.25.21>{{cite web|url=https://www.flickeringmyth.com/titan-hard-case-crime-announce-gun-honey/|title=Titan and Hard Case Crime announce Gun Honey|publisher=Flickering Myth|author=Collinson, Gary|language=en-US|url-status=live|date=June 25, 2021|access-date=May 18, 2024|archive-date=May 18, 2024|archive-url=https://archive.ph/jiAu4}}</ref> and he has likened ''Gun Honey'' to other espionage action thrillers that influenced it, such as [[James Bond]],<ref name=FreakSugar>{{cite web|url=https://www.freaksugar.com/interview-charles-ardai-on-illusion-danger-in-heat-seeker-a-gun-honey-series/|publisher=Freak Sugar|title=INTERVIEW: CHARLES ARDAI ON ILLUSION & DANGER IN HEAT SEEKER: A GUN HONEY SERIES!|author=Keith, Jed W.|language=en-US|url-status=live|date=April 28, 2023|access-date=May 18, 2024|archive-date=May 18, 2024|archive-url=https://archive.ph/13JzB}}</ref> as well as action/adventure stories featuring female protagonists, such as [[Modesty Blaise]], ''[[Alias (TV series)|Alias]]'', ''[[Kill Bill]]'',<ref name=CBR6.25.21/> and ''[[Barbarella (comics)|Barbarella]]''.<ref name=FreakSugar/> At the review aggregator website Comic Book Roundup, the debut issue has a rating of 8 out of 10, based on eight critics' reviews.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://comicbookroundup.com/comic-books/reviews/titan-books/gun-honey/1|title=Gun Honey #1|publisher=Comic Book Roundup|language=en-US|url-status=live|date=September 29, 2021|access-date=May 18, 2024|archive-date=September 29, 2021|archive-url=https://archive.ph/qkfYF}}</ref> The series was collected in [[trade paperback (comics)|trade paperback]] form in May 2023 under the title ''Gun Honey: Honey for Blood''. The story was followed by a sequel, ''Gun Honey: Blood for Blood'', in which Joanna and her ally, a government agent named Brook Barrow, are framed for murder.<ref name=FreakSugar/> That miniseries premiered August 24, 2022.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://leagueofcomicgeeks.com/comics/series/156628/gun-honey-blood-for-blood|title=Gun Honey: Blood for Blood|publisher=League of Comic Geeks|language=en-US|url-status=live|date=August 24, 2022|access-date=May 18, 2024|archive-date=May 18, 2024|archive-url=https://archive.ph/dxJwL}}</ref> This was in turn followed by a four-issue spinoff series, ''Heat Seeker: A Gun Honey Series'', also written by Ardai, with art by Ace Continuado, Jose Zapata, and Asifur Rahman. The book, whose debut issue was released on June 28, 2023, sees Tan going on the run after she is targeted for assassination by the U.S. government. Pursued by a beautiful sociopath hitwoman named Sarah Claride, Tan seeks help from her friend, stage magician and illusionist Dahlia Racers, who specializes in helping people disappear.<ref name=FreakSugar/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cbr.com/titan-comics-gun-honey-spinoff-heat-seeker/|title=EXCLUSIVE: Titan's Pulp Spy Thriller Gun Honey Expands With New Spinoff Series|publisher=[[CBR.com]]|author=Schreuer, Brandon|language=en-US|url-status=live|date=February 20, 2023|access-date=May 18, 2024|archive-date=May 18, 2024|archive-url=https://archive.ph/tcHkJ}}</ref> The next installment in the series was the three-issue ''Gun Honey: Collision Course'', whose debut issue was released May 15, 2024.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://leagueofcomicgeeks.com/comics/series/174445/gun-honey-collision-course|title=Gun Honey: Collision Course|publisher=League of Comic Geeks|language=en-US|url-status=live|date=May 15, 2024|access-date=May 18, 2024|archive-date=May 18, 2024|archive-url=https://archive.ph/pMH3P}}</ref>

old_content: The main [[Religion in Nauru|religion practised on the island]] is [[Christianity]]: the main denominations are [[Nauru Congregational Church]] (35.71%), [[Roman Catholic]]ism (32.96%), [[Assemblies of God]] (12.98%, and [[Baptist]] (1.48%).<ref name="state"/> The Constitution provides for [[freedom of religion]]. The government has restricted the religious practices of [[the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints]] and the [[Jehovah's Witnesses]], most of whom are foreign workers employed by the government-owned Nauru Phosphate Corporation.<ref>{{cite web |publisher=US Department of State |year=2003 |url=https://2001-2009.state.gov/g/drl/rls/irf/2003/24314.htm |work=International Religious Freedom Report 2003 |title=Nauru |accessdate=2 May 2005}}</ref> The Catholics are pastorally served by the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Tarawa and Nauru]], with see at [[Tarawa]] in Kiribati.

old_content: Shen Dao makes some use of fa akin to law, but generally uses fa objective standards in a manner similar to Shen Buhai, as an administrative technique. He uses fa standards as a administrative technique to determine reward and punishment in accordance with merit. [[Xun Kuang]] refers to his opponents as obsessed with particular aspects of the way, and refers to Shen Dao as obsessed with the emulation of models rather than the employment of worthy men. He criticizes him as respecting the imitation of models more broadly, but not necessarily following them with the assumption that only one is correct. He WAS more concerned in his time that there are laws than their particulars. According to Xun Kuang, his laws (or more literally, models) lack 'proper foundations', and will not be successful in ordering the state. He  wasn't concerned that he advocated fa/law itself.{{sfnm|1a1=Goldin|1y=2011|1p=8(98)|2a1=Rubin|2y=1974|2p=343|3a1=Hansen|3y=1992|3p=317|4a1=Harris|4y=2017|4p=75}}
new_content: Although often translated as law, Shen Dao more accurately makes some use of fa akin to law. He generally uses fa objective standards in a manner similar to Shen Buhai, as an administrative technique, but uses them to determine reward and punishment in accordance with merit. [[Xun Kuang]] refers to his opponents as obsessed with particular aspects of the way, and refers to Shen Dao as obsessed with the emulation of models rather than the employment of worthy men. He criticizes him as respecting the imitation of models more broadly, but not necessarily following them with the assumption that only one is correct. He WAS more concerned in his time that there are laws than their particulars. According to Xun Kuang, his laws (or more literally, models) lack 'proper foundations', and will not be successful in ordering the state. He  wasn't concerned that he advocated fa/law itself.{{sfnm|1a1=Goldin|1y=2011|1p=8(98)|2a1=Rubin|2y=1974|2p=343|3a1=Hansen|3y=1992|3p=317|4a1=Harris|4y=2017|4p=75}}

old_content: The '''metatarsophalangeal joints''' ('''MTP joints'''), also informally known as '''toe [[knuckle]]s''', are the [[joint]]s between the [[metatarsal bones]] of the foot and the proximal bones ([[proximal phalanges]]) of the [[toe]]s. They are  [[condyloid joint]]s, meaning that an elliptical or rounded surface (of the metatarsal bones) comes close to a shallow cavity (of the proximal phalanges).
new_content: The '''metatarsophalangeal joints''' ('''MTP joints''') are the [[joint]]s between the [[metatarsal bones]] of the foot and the proximal bones ([[proximal phalanges]]) of the [[toe]]s. They are analogous to the [[knuckle]]s of the [[hand]], and are consequently known as '''toe knuckles''' in common speech. They are  [[condyloid joint]]s, meaning that an elliptical or rounded surface (of the metatarsal bones) comes close to a shallow cavity (of the proximal phalanges).

old_content: Swift recorded ''Lover'' after finishing her 2018 [[Reputation Stadium Tour]], having recalibrated her personal life and artistic direction following the public controversies that preceded her previous studio album, ''[[Reputation (album)|Reputation]]'' (2017). She produced ''Lover'' with [[Jack Antonoff]], [[Joel Little]], [[Louis Bell]], and [[Frank Dukes]]. Described by Swift as a "lover letter to love", the album explores wide-ranging emotions like infatuation, commitment, lust, and heartache; a few songs discuss political issues such as [[LGBT rights in the United States|LGBT rights]] and [[feminism]]. The production incorporates a 1980s-inspired [[electropop]], [[pop rock]], and [[synth-pop]] sound characterized by atmospheric [[synthesizer]]s, mid-tempo rhythms, and acoustic instruments, with eclectic elements of [[country music|country]], [[folk music|folk]], and [[funk]].
new_content: Swift recorded ''Lover'' after finishing her 2018 [[Reputation Stadium Tour]], having recalibrated her personal life and artistic direction following the public controversies that preceded her previous studio album, ''[[Reputation (album)|Reputation]]'' (2017). old_content: In December 1696, a group of sailors from the [[Caroline Islands]] were stranded on [[Samar]], near [[Guiuan|Guiuan,]] when they met European missionary [[Pablo Clain|Paul Klein]]. Using pebbles, the sailors attempted to show Klein the approximate location and size of the islands. He used this information to produce the first European map of the Palau area. Klein sent the map to [[Superior General of the Society of Jesus|Jesuit Superior General]], along with a letter detailing the names of the islands, the culture of the people, and his experiences with them.<ref>{{Cite journal |last1=Hezel |first1=Francis X. |last2=Valle |first2=Maria Teresa Del |date=1972 |title=Early European Contact with the Western Carolines: 1525-1750 |url=https://www.jstor.org/stable/25168089 |journal=The Journal of Pacific History |volume=7 |pages=26–44 |doi=10.1080/00223347208572199 |jstor=25168089 |issn=0022-3344}}</ref>
new_content: In December 1696, a group of sailors from the [[Caroline Islands]] were stranded on [[Samar]], near [[Guiuan]], when they met European missionary [[Pablo Clain|Paul Klein]]. Using pebbles, the sailors attempted to show Klein the approximate location and size of the islands. He used this information to produce the first European map of the Palau area. Klein sent the map to [[Superior General of the Society of Jesus|Jesuit Superior General]], along with a letter detailing the names of the islands, the culture of the people, and his experiences with them.<ref>{{Cite journal |last1=Hezel |first1=Francis X. |last2=Valle |first2=Maria Teresa Del |date=1972 |title=Early European Contact with the Western Carolines: 1525-1750 |url=https://www.jstor.org/stable/25168089 |journal=The Journal of Pacific History |volume=7 |pages=26–44 |doi=10.1080/00223347208572199 |jstor=25168089 |issn=0022-3344}}</ref>

old_content: Miller was suspended, along with eight other players, his first year at Florida in 2017 due to felony fraud charges.<ref name="espn">{{Cite web |last=Aschoff |first=Edward |date=January 23, 2018 |title=Sources: 4 suspended players to rejoin Gators|agency=Associated Press |url=https://www.espn.com/college-football/story/_/id/22191464/florida-gators-allow-4-suspended-players-rejoin-team |access-date=October 24, 2023 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref> He returned from the suspension in 2018 and appeared in all 13 games recording 15 tackles, one sack and one interception which he returned 82 yards for a touchdown. Miller became a starter his sophomore year in 2019, starting 11 of 12 games and finishing with 55 tackles and three sacks. Miller has reportedly been dating a law student since 2021. <ref name="gatorsports">{{Cite web |last=Hall |first=Graham |date=September 8, 2020 |title=Ventrell Miller embracing opportunity to lead in middle of Gators' defense |url=https://www.gatorsports.com/story/football/2020/09/08/miller-embracing-opportunity-lead-middle-gators-defense/5743425002/ |access-date=October 24, 2023 |website=Gator Sports |language=en-US}}</ref> He returned as a starter his junior year in 2020.<ref name="heraldtribune">{{Cite web |last=Hall |first=Graham |date=August 25, 2019 |title=Miller vital in Gators' dominant defensive performance |url=https://www.news-journalonline.com/story/sports/college/football/2019/08/25/miller-vital-in-gators-dominant-defensive-performance/4372352007/ |access-date=October 24, 2023 |website=Daytona Beach News-Journal Online |language=en-US}}</ref><ref name="orlandosentinel">{{Cite web |last=Thompson |first=Edgar |date=September 2, 2020 |title=Gator's Ventrell Miller ready to lead defense |url=https://www.orlandosentinel.com/sports/florida-gators/os-sp-gators-football-vetrell-miller-0903-20200902-nk5slqwzu5a5nixaexfd4yvene-story.html |access-date=October 14, 2020 |website=Orlando Sentinel}}</ref>

old_content: On 28 August 2013, after about a month on the run that started after his June 2013 conviction,<ref name="ANSA 2014"/> Matacena was arrested in Dubai,<ref>{{Cite web |date=29 August 2013 |title='Ndrangheta: ex deputato Fi Amedeo Matacena fermato a Dubai<!-- - Cronaca--> |url=http://www.ansamed.info/ansamed/it/notizie/rubriche/cronaca/2013/08/29/-Ndrangheta-ex-deputato-Fi-Amedeo-Matacena-fermato-Dubai_9214347.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130901084415/http://ansa.it/ansamed/it/notizie/rubriche/cronaca/2013/08/29/-Ndrangheta-ex-deputato-Fi-Amedeo-Matacena-fermato-Dubai_9214347.html |archive-date=1 September 2013 |access-date=18 May 2024 |website=ANSAMed |language=it}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=29 August 2013 |title=Arrestato a Dubai l'ex deputato Matacena |url=http://www.corriere.it/cronache/13_agosto_29/ex-deputato-matacena-latitante-arrestato-dubai_75052eb0-1089-11e3-abea-779a600e18b3.shtml |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220524191948/https://www.corriere.it/cronache/13_agosto_29/ex-deputato-matacena-latitante-arrestato-dubai_75052eb0-1089-11e3-abea-779a600e18b3.shtml |archive-date=24 May 2022 |access-date=18 May 2024 |website=Corriere della Sera |language=it}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=31 August 2013 |title='Ndrangheta: fermato a Dubai l'ex deputato Matacena |url=https://www.liberoquotidiano.it/news/cronaca/1301037/ndrangheta-fermato-a-dubai-lex-deputato-matacena.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240518132004/https://www.liberoquotidiano.it/news/cronaca/1301037/ndrangheta-fermato-a-dubai-lex-deputato-matacena.html |archive-date=18 May 2024 |access-date=18 May 2024 |website=Libero |language=it}}</ref> where he arrived from the [[Seychelles]],<ref name="ANSA 2014"/> by the [[Interpol]] and the arrest section of the investigative unit of the ''Carabinieri'' of Reggio Calabria.<ref>{{cite web |date=29 August 2013 |title='Ndrangheta, arrestato Matacena. L'ex deputato era latitante a Dubai |url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2013/08/29/news/arrestato_a_dubai_l_ex_deputato_matacena-65473976/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231005045706/https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2013/08/29/news/arrestato_a_dubai_l_ex_deputato_matacena-65473976/ |archive-date=5 October 2023 |access-date=18 May 2024 |website=La Repubblica |language=it}}</ref> He was released by the authorities of the United Arab Emirates in October 2013, with a ban on leaving the country, and thus denied the extradition.<ref>{{cite web |last=Ruotolo |first=Guido |date=9 May 2014 |title='Favorì un latitante' |url=https://www.lastampa.it/politica/2014/05/09/news/favori-un-latitante-1.35752343/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211202105203/https://www.lastampa.it/politica/2014/05/09/news/favori-un-latitante-1.35752343 |archive-date=2 December 2021 |access-date=18 May 2024 |website=La Stampa |language=it}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=13 July 2014 |title=Rigettata estradizione Matacena<!-- - Notizie - Ansa.it--> |url=https://www.ansa.it/calabria/notizie/2014/07/13/rigettata-estradizione-matacena_5428b338-fc1f-416e-bb1e-1f28c2f1e034.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240518030254/https://ansabrasil.com.br/calabria/notizie/2014/07/13/rigettata-estradizione-matacena_5428b338-fc1f-416e-bb1e-1f28c2f1e034.html |archive-date=18 May 2024 |access-date=18 May 2024 |website=Agenzia ANSA |language=it}}</ref> On 8 May 2014, Scajola was arrested by the [[Anti-Mafia Investigation Division]] of Reggio Calabria on charges of having favoured Matacena's fugitive status and of wanting to plan his transfer to Lebanon.<ref>{{cite web |date=8 May 2014 |title=Scajola non risponde al gip. Matacena: 'Sono innocente'<!-- - Politica--> |url=https://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/politica/2014/05/08/arrestato-ex-ministro-scajola_10bc0bdd-45a0-4c77-9368-83be1f6df243.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211208012732/https://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/politica/2014/05/08/arrestato-ex-ministro-scajola_10bc0bdd-45a0-4c77-9368-83be1f6df243.html |archive-date=8 December 2021 |access-date=18 May 2024 |website=Agenzia ANSA |language=it}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Macrì |first=Carlo |date=8 May 2014 |title=Arrestati l'ex ministro Scajola e l'ex deputato di Forza Italia Matacena |url=http://www.corriere.it/cronache/14_maggio_08/arrestato-l-ex-ministro-scajola-l-ex-deputato-forza-italia-matacena-fa234332-d674-11e3-b1c6-d3130b63f531.shtml |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211219162308/https://www.corriere.it/cronache/14_maggio_08/arrestato-l-ex-ministro-scajola-l-ex-deputato-forza-italia-matacena-fa234332-d674-11e3-b1c6-d3130b63f531.shtml |archive-date=19 December 2021 |access-date=18 May 2024 |website=Corriere della Sera |language=it}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Rinaldi |first=Luca |date=8 May 2014 |title=Matacena e i guai di Scajola con le cosche |url=https://www.linkiesta.it/2014/05/matacena-e-i-guai-di-scajola-con-le-cosche/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240518013507/https://www.linkiesta.it/2014/05/matacena-e-i-guai-di-scajola-con-le-cosche/ |archive-date=18 May 2024 |access-date=18 May 2024 |website=Linkiesta.it |language=it}}</ref> The precautionary custody order in prison was also issued for his factotum Martino Politi; under a house arrest order were placed for his mother Raffaella De Carolis,<ref>{{cite web |last=Turano |first=Gianfrancesco |date=8 May 2014 |title=Arrestato l'ex ministro Claudio Scajola: ha favorito la latitanza dell'ex deputato Pdl Amedeo Matacena |url=http://espresso.repubblica.it/palazzo/2014/05/08/news/claudio-scajola-arrestato-avrebbe-aiutato-nella-latitanza-l-ex-deputato-pdl-amedeo-matacena-1.164379 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220121212325/https://espresso.repubblica.it/palazzo/2014/05/08/news/claudio-scajola-arrestato-avrebbe-aiutato-nella-latitanza-l-ex-deputato-pdl-amedeo-matacena-1.164379/ |archive-date=21 January 2022 |access-date=18 May 2024 |website=L'Espresso |language=it}}</ref> his secretary Maria Grazia Fiordalisi, Scajola's secretary Roberta Sacco, and for Rizzo, Matacena's wife.<ref>{{cite web |date=9 May 2014 |title=Arrestato l'ex ministro Claudio Scajola 'Ha aiutato ex deputato latitante'<!-- - Cronaca Italiana - L'Unione Sarda--> |url=http://www.unionesarda.it/articoli/articolo/366537 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140512221427/http://www.unionesarda.it/articoli/articolo/366537 |archive-date=12 May 2014 |access-date=18 May 2024 |website=L'Unione Sarda}}</ref> Rizzo, who was unavailable at the time of the execution of the restrictive measure against her, was arrested in [[Nice]] on 11 May 2014;<ref>{{cite web |date=12 May 2014 |title=Caso Scajola, moglie di Matacena pronta a rimpatriare 'Le intercettazioni? Pronta a spiegare tutto' |url=http://ilquotidianodellacalabria.it/news/cronache/725340/Caso-Scajola--moglie-di-Matacena.html |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140512063306/http://ilquotidianodellacalabria.it/news/cronache/725340/Caso-Scajola--moglie-di-Matacena.html |archive-date=12 May 2014 |access-date=18 May 2024 |website=Il Quotidiano della Calabria |language=it}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Ruotolo |first=Guido |date=22 June 2014 |title=Matacena: 'Mia moglie in carcere per ricattarmi. Liberatela e mi consegno' |url=https://www.lastampa.it/cronaca/2014/06/22/news/matacena-mia-moglie-in-carcere-per-ricattarmi-liberatela-e-mi-consegno-1.35746672/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191219203216/https://www.lastampa.it/cronaca/2014/06/22/news/matacena-mia-moglie-in-carcere-per-ricattarmi-liberatela-e-mi-consegno-1.35746672 |archive-date=19 December 2019 |access-date=18 May 2024 |website=La Stampa |language=it}}</ref> On 24 January 2020, Scajola and Rizzo were respectively sentenced to two and one years in the first instance trial;<ref name="Bongiovanni 2022"/><ref name="Rai News 2022"/> Scajola's sentence was suspended and the aggravating circumstance of having favored the mafia was excluded, while one of Rizzo's charges was extinguished due to the statute of limitations.<ref>{{cite web |last=Serio |first=Alessandra |date=24 January 2020 |title=Latitanza Matacena, condanna ad un anno per Chiara Rizzo |url=https://www.tempostretto.it/news/latitanza-matacena-condanna-ad-un-anno-per-chiara-rizzo.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200919193648/https://www.tempostretto.it/news/latitanza-matacena-condanna-ad-un-anno-per-chiara-rizzo.html |archive-date=19 September 2020 |access-date=18 May 2024 |website=Tempo Stretto<!-- - Ultime notizie da Messina e Reggio Calabria--> |language=it}}</ref> In motivating the sentence, the judges wrote that "an interest in helping Matacena to obtain political asylum in Lebanon emerged following a request from his wife Chiara Rizzo", and that Scajola's conduct "did not end in lawful aid to the fugitive" due to the existence of "undoubted and consolidated" relationships.<ref>{{cite web |date=27 May 2020 |title='Aiuto Scajola a Matacena non lecito' |url=https://it.euronews.com/2020/05/27/aiuto-scajola-a-matacena-non-lecito |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230205190232/https://it.euronews.com/2020/05/27/aiuto-scajola-a-matacena-non-lecito |archive-date=5 February 2023 |access-date=18 April 2024 |website=Euronews |language=it}}</ref>

Pronta a spiegare tutto' |url=http://ilquotidianodellacalabria.it/news/cronache/725340/Caso-Scajola--moglie-di-Matacena.html |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140512063306/http://ilquotidianodellacalabria.it/news/cronache/725340/Caso-Scajola--moglie-di-Matacena.html |archive-date=12 May 2014 |access-date=18 May 2024 |website=Il Quotidiano della Calabria |language=it}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Ruotolo |first=Guido |date=22 June 2014 |title=Matacena: 'Mia moglie in carcere per ricattarmi. Liberatela e mi consegno' |url=https://www.lastampa.it/cronaca/2014/06/22/news/matacena-mia-moglie-in-carcere-per-ricattarmi-liberatela-e-mi-consegno-1.35746672/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191219203216/https://www.lastampa.it/cronaca/2014/06/22/news/matacena-mia-moglie-in-carcere-per-ricattarmi-liberatela-e-mi-consegno-1.35746672 |archive-date=19 December 2019 |access-date=18 May 2024 |website=La Stampa |language=it}}</ref> On 24 January 2020, Scajola and Rizzo were respectively sentenced to two and one years in the first instance trial;<ref name="Bongiovanni 2022"/><ref name="Rai News 2022"/> Scajola's sentence was suspended and the aggravating circumstance of having favored the mafia was excluded, while one of Rizzo's charges was extinguished due to the statute of limitations.<ref>{{cite web |last=Serio |first=Alessandra |date=24 January 2020 |title=Latitanza Matacena, condanna ad un anno per Chiara Rizzo |url=https://www.tempostretto.it/news/latitanza-matacena-condanna-ad-un-anno-per-chiara-rizzo.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200919193648/https://www.tempostretto.it/news/latitanza-matacena-condanna-ad-un-anno-per-chiara-rizzo.html |archive-date=19 September 2020 |access-date=18 May 2024 |website=Tempo Stretto<!-- - Ultime notizie da Messina e Reggio Calabria--> |language=it}}</ref> In motivating the sentence, the judges wrote that "an interest in helping Matacena to obtain political asylum in Lebanon emerged following a request from his wife Chiara Rizzo", and that Scajola's conduct "did not end in lawful aid to the fugitive" due to the existence of "undoubted and consolidated" relationships.<ref>{{cite web |date=27 May 2020 |title='Aiuto Scajola a Matacena non lecito' |url=https://it.euronews.com/2020/05/27/aiuto-scajola-a-matacena-non-lecito |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230205190232/https://it.euronews.com/2020/05/27/aiuto-scajola-a-matacena-non-lecito |archive-date=5 February 2023 |access-date=18 April 2024 |website=Euronews |language=it}}</ref>

old_content: The [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour Party]] maintained control of the council, with their seat count holding steady. For the third year in a row, the [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative Party]] lost three seats, all to Labour; the party would additionally lose a seat in Pudsey two days after the election when Trish Smith, elected the previous year, resigned to sit as an independent.<ref>[https://westleedsdispatch.com/pudsey-councillor-trish-smith-quits-conservative-party/ Pudsey councillor Trish Smith quits Conservative party]</ref> The [[Green Party of England and Wales|Green Party]] also succeeded in taking three seats from Labour and saw the largest popular vote share increase out of any of the parties, though Labour in turn unseated Green group leader David Blackburn, preventing the Greens from equalling the [[Liberal Democrats (UK)|Liberal Democrats]] as the third-largest group on the council. The [[Social Democratic Party (UK, 1990–present)|Social Democratic Party]] took the third seat in Middleton Park, wiping out the Labour Party's representation in the ward, and all other parties held level in their seat count.
new_content: The [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour Party]] maintained control of the council, with their seat count holding steady. For the third year in a row, the [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative Party]] lost three seats, all to Labour; the party would additionally lose a seat in Pudsey two days after the election when Trish Smith, re-elected the previous year, resigned to sit as an independent.<ref>[https://westleedsdispatch.com/pudsey-councillor-trish-smith-quits-conservative-party/ Pudsey councillor Trish Smith quits Conservative party]</ref> The [[Green Party of England and Wales|Green Party]] also succeeded in taking three seats from Labour and saw the largest popular vote share increase out of any of the parties, though Labour in turn unseated Green group leader David Blackburn, preventing the Greens from equalling the [[Liberal Democrats (UK)|Liberal Democrats]] as the third-largest group on the council. The [[Social Democratic Party (UK, 1990–present)|Social Democratic Party]] took the third seat in Middleton Park, wiping out the Labour Party's representation in the ward, and all other parties held level in their seat count.

Even against Shajarian's will, the state TV and [[Radio broadcasting|radio stations]] stopped airing ''Rabbana'', a [[prayer]] sung during the Muslim fasting month of [[Ramadan]] heralding the moment of fast-breaking.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.npr.org/2020/10/08/808232631/a-voice-of-iran-master-singer-mohammad-reza-shajarian-has-died|title=A Voice of Iran, Master Singer Mohammad Reza Shajarian, Has Died|newspaper=NPR|date=8 October 2020|last1=Tsioulcas|first1=Anastasia}}</ref> The recital had been broadcast regularly every Ramadan since the 1979 revolution but swept from public view after the legendary singer fell out of favor with the establishment. Despite these events, Fr. Pierz considered the resentments felt by the Ojibwe and Dakota to be perfectly understandable.<ref> Robert J. Voigt, ''Pierzana II: The Religious and Secular History of Pierz, Minnesota'', Self Published. Pages 15-16.</ref> For example, in a September 1862 letter, Fr. Pierz expressed his thoughts about [[Battles of New Ulm|the recent destruction]] of [[New Ulm, Minnesota]] during two recent battles between local German-American settlers and the [[Dakota people]]. Fr. Pierz described a recent New Ulm festival and parade which were, from a Catholic perspective, a very deliberate and insulting mockery of [[Corpus Christi]] [[Eucharistic procession]]s and the doctrine of the [[Real Presence]] by the [[anti-clericalism|anti-clerical]] German-American [[Freethinkers]] and [[Forty-Eighters]] who had founded and still dominated that settlement. Fr Pierz expressed a belief that the attack may have represented divine retribution for both the [[anti-Catholicism in the United States|anti-Catholic]] festival parade and for what he considered the dishonorable behavior of local settlers' and corrupt Federal Indian Agents.<ref> [https://athrillingnarrative.com/2013/04/01/the-scourge-of-god-against-german-infidels/ "The Scourge of God" on German "Infidels"]</ref>

old_content: In 2016, a mid-career survey of García Torres’ work was held at the [[Museo Rufino Tamayo]] and in three other venues in Mexico City. Theoretically, the works in the show were exhibited in the geographic area that would be covered if you would superimposed the Museo de Arte Sacramento -a "museum without walls" in the state of [[Coahuila]], Mexico, conceived by the artist between 2002 and 2004- over a section of the city. According to Leslie Moody Castro "Within this fantastically complex exhibition, Garcia Torres blurs any standards regarding linear time or functional space, ultimately offering an opportunity to reconsider our understanding of reality".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Moody Castro |first1=Leslie |title=Mario García Torres |url=https://www.artforum.com/picks/mario-garcia-torres-59587 |website=Artforum |accessdate=30 June 2020}}</ref>"Let's Walk Together" was curated by Sofia Hernández Chong-Cuy.
new_content: In 2016, a mid-career survey of García Torres’ work was held at the [[Museo Rufino Tamayo, Mexico City|Museo Rufino Tamayo]] and in three other venues in Mexico City. Theoretically, the works in the show were exhibited in the geographic area that would be covered if you would superimposed the Museo de Arte Sacramento -a "museum without walls" in the state of [[Coahuila]], Mexico, conceived by the artist between 2002 and 2004- over a section of the city. According to Leslie Moody Castro "Within this fantastically complex exhibition, Garcia Torres blurs any standards regarding linear time or functional space, ultimately offering an opportunity to reconsider our understanding of reality".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Moody Castro |first1=Leslie |title=Mario García Torres |url=https://www.artforum.com/picks/mario-garcia-torres-59587 |website=Artforum |accessdate=30 June 2020}}</ref>"Let's Walk Together" was curated by Sofia Hernández Chong-Cuy.

old_content: The [[Australian Bureau of Statistics]] does not collect data on [[race (human categorization)|race]], but asks each Australian resident to nominate up to two [[ancestry|ancestries]] each [[Census in Australia|census]].<ref name="Understanding and using Ancestry da">{{Cite web | url=https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/detailed-methodology-information/information-papers/understanding-and-using-ancestry-data | title=Understanding and using Ancestry data |website=Australian Bureau of Statistics | date=28 June 2022 |url-status=live |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20240209190954/https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/detailed-methodology-information/information-papers/understanding-and-using-ancestry-data |archive-date= Feb 9, 2024 }}</ref> These ancestry responses are classified into broad standardised ancestry groups.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/classifications/australian-standard-classification-cultural-and-ethnic-groups-ascceg/latest-release | title=Australian Standard Classification of Cultural and Ethnic Groups (ASCCEG), 2019 |website=Australian Bureau of Statistics | date=18 December 2019 |url-status=live |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20231121023512/https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/classifications/australian-standard-classification-cultural-and-ethnic-groups-ascceg/latest-release |archive-date=  Nov 21, 2023 }}</ref> At the 2021 census, the number of ancestry responses within each standardised group as a proportion of the total population was as follows:<ref name="abs.gov.au">[https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/people/people-and-communities/cultural-diversity-census/2021/Cultural%20diversity%20data%20summary.xlsx Cultural diversity data summary]. 2021. Australian Bureau of Statistics.</ref> 57.2% [[European Australians|European]] (including 46% [[Northwestern Europe#Ethnographic definitions|North-West European]] and 11.2% [[Southern Europe|Southern]] and [[Eastern Europe]]an), 33.8% [[Demographics of Oceania|Oceanian]],{{Refn|group="N"|Includes those who nominate "Australian" as their ancestry. The Australian Bureau of Statistics has stated that most who nominate "Australian" as their ancestry have at least partial [[Anglo-Celtic Australian|Anglo-Celtic]] [[European Australian|European]] ancestry.<ref name="Commonwealth of Australia">{{Cite news|url=http://www.abs.gov.au/Ausstats/abs@.nsf/94713ad445ff1425ca25682000192af2/49f609c83cf34d69ca2569de0025c182!OpenDocument |title=Feature Article – Ethnic and Cultural Diversity in Australia (Feature Article) |publisher=Commonwealth of Australia |agency=[[Australian Bureau of Statistics]] |work=1301.0 – Year Book Australia, 1995}}</ref>}} 17.4% [[Asian Australians|Asian]] (including 6.5% [[South Asia|Southern]] and [[Central Asia#Demographics|Central Asian]], 6.4% [[East Asia|North-East Asian]], and 4.5% [[Southeast Asia|South-East Asian]]), 3.2% [[Demographics of the Middle East and North Africa|North African and Middle Eastern]], 1.4% [[Americas#Demography|Peoples of the Americas]], and 1.3% [[Sub-Saharan Africa#Demographics|Sub-Saharan African]]. Australian Bureau of Statistics.</ref> 57.2% [[European Australians|European]] (including 46% [[Northwestern Europe#Ethnographic definitions|North-West European]] and 11.2% [[Southern Europe|Southern]] and [[Eastern Europe]]an), 33.8% [[Demographics of Oceania|Oceanian]],{{Refn|group="N"|Includes those who nominate "Australian" as their ancestry.<ref name="Stat"/> The Australian Bureau of Statistics has stated that most who nominate "Australian" as their ancestry have at least partial [[Anglo-Celtic Australian|Anglo-Celtic]] [[European Australian|European]] ancestry.<ref name="Commonwealth of Australia">{{Cite news|url=http://www.abs.gov.au/Ausstats/abs@.nsf/94713ad445ff1425ca25682000192af2/49f609c83cf34d69ca2569de0025c182!OpenDocument |title=Feature Article – Ethnic and Cultural Diversity in Australia (Feature Article) |publisher=Commonwealth of Australia |agency=[[Australian Bureau of Statistics]] |work=1301.0 – Year Book Australia, 1995}}</ref>}} 17.4% [[Asian Australians|Asian]] (including 6.5% [[South Asia|Southern]] and [[Central Asia#Demographics|Central Asian]], 6.4% [[East Asia|North-East Asian]], and 4.5% [[Southeast Asia|South-East Asian]]), 3.2% [[Demographics of the Middle East and North Africa|North African and Middle Eastern]], 1.4% [[Americas#Demography|Peoples of the Americas]], and 1.3% [[Sub-Saharan Africa#Demographics|Sub-Saharan African]]. new_content: One group exhibition held at the [[Housatonic Museum of Art]] was reviewed by ''[[The New York Times]]'', which said Rodriguez-Diaz was inspired by [[Salvador Dalí]].<ref name=dali>{{cite news | url=https://www.proquest.com/docview/427748946 | title=Prints and Drawings By Latin Americans | work=The New York Times | date=July 1, 1990 | accessdate=December 10, 2023 | author=Raynor, Vivien | pages=A22| id={{ProQuest|427748946}} }}</ref> Rodriguez-Diaz lived in New York City for 16 years, before moving to San Antonio where he focused not only on paintings, but public art installations as well.<ref name=oral/><ref name=morgan/> He immediately felt a connection to [[Mexican Americans]] in the area, as he saw them as a colonized people, like Puerto Ricans.<ref name=oral/> In 1998, he created an installation at Artpace in San Antonio that drew parallels between the Spanish American War and the Mexican War, including the rallying cries of "Remember the Maine" and "Remember the Alamo."<ref>Heartney, Eleanor (1998). old_content: Perez was the subject of a failed [[recall election|recall]] in mid-2006, which was coordinated by the Sheboygan branch of Citizens for Responsible Government. The recall effort had a racial tone to their recall effort<ref>{{cite news |title=Racist undertones cloud recall effort in Sheboygan |url=http://www.jsonline.com/story/index.aspx?id=475121 |access-date=5 March 2021 |issue=July 21, 2006 |publisher=Milwaukee Journal Sentinel|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20070929133522/http://www.jsonline.com/story/index.aspx?id=475121|archive-date = 2007-09-29}}</ref> but the group claimed that Perez "fail(ed) to uphold his mayoral duties in office with integrity and professionalism," based on his successful efforts to move the location of the city's new police headquarters from a local park to a site on the city's west side, and an aborted merge of the Sheboygan Police Department and 911 center into the [[Sheboygan County Sheriff's Office]], along with issues regarding coverage of the city from local radio station [[WHBL]] and the city's decision to market tourism through their own city division rather than through the Sheboygan County Chamber of Commerce.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://recall.sheboyganspirit.com/reasons.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-05-04 |url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090105210330/http://recall.sheboyganspirit.com/reasons.html |archivedate=2009-01-05 }}</ref> 6,000 signatures were needed, but supposedly only 4,013 of the signatures required, were collected. None of the signatures were ever confirmed or verified.

old_content: Hinderlie regularly performs at venues and festivals in the United States, particularly in New Orleans, and held a residency at the Pelican Club in the city's [[French Quarter]] for 25 years (1991–2016). His performances have extended beyond the United States to venues in Germany, Panama, Denmark, the Netherlands, Singapore, Hong Kong, and Japan. He has also appeared as a guest artist at events like the Yerevan International Jazz Festival in Armenia, the United States Embassy in Tbilisi, Georgia, and the Schloss Lingerberg in Dresden, Germany. One of his solo jazz piano concerts from 2011 has gained  over 250,000 views on YouTube.<ref>{{cite web|title=Loyola Jazz Piano Concert, July 2011| website=[[YouTube]] |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5_rTms8ebC8}}</ref>

old_content: '''Nghana tamu Lewis''' is a judge, scholar, lawyer and tenured associate professor from [[Lafayette, Louisiana]].<ref name="special.to-2021">{{Cite web |last=special.to |date=2021-02-18 |title=Black History Month:Celebrate Judge Nghana Lewis |url=https://www.lobservateur.com/2021/02/18/black-history-monthcelebrate-judge-nghana-lewis/ |access-date=2023-10-07 |website=L'Observateur |language=en}}</ref> In January 2021, Lewis took the bench to serve as the Division B 40th District Court judge, in [[St. John the Baptist Parish, Louisiana|St. John the Baptist Parish]], Louisiana.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Robichaux |first=Brooke |date=2020-11-07 |title=Meet your 40th Judicial District Judges |url=https://www.lobservateur.com/2020/11/07/meet-your-40th-judicial-district-judges/ |access-date=2023-12-11 |website=L'Observateur |language=en}}</ref> Lewis is also a tenured associate professor in both the English Department and the Africana Studies Department at [[Tulane University]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2014-10-19 |title=Alumni Profile: Dr. Nghana Lewis |url=https://www.louisianayouthseminar.org/blog/2014/10/19/alumni-profile |access-date=2023-12-11 |website=Louisiana Youth Seminar |language=en-US}}</ref>

old_content: A memorial statue by sculptor [[William McMillan (sculptor)|William McMillan]] was erected at [[London Heathrow Airport]] in 1954 to celebrate their flight. The statue was taken to Ireland as part of the centenary celebrations in 2019 before being relocated at [[Brooklands Museum]], where it was formally unveiled in February 2020<ref>{{Cite web |date=11 February 2020 |title=Statue Honouring Pioneers of Flight Unveiled at Brooklands Museum |url=https://www.brooklandsmuseum.com/about/latest-news/statue-honouring-pioneers-of-flight-unveiled-at-brooklands-museum}}</ref>. There is also a monument at [[Manchester Airport]], less than 8 miles from John Alcock's birthplace. Their aircraft (rebuilt by the Vickers Company) is located in the [[Science Museum, London|Science Museum]] in [[South Kensington]], [[London]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Alcock and Brown's Vickers Vimy biplane |url=https://collection.sciencemuseumgroup.org.uk/objects/co499537}}</ref>

The [[Sikhs|Sikh]] community in [[Trinidad and Tobago]], numbering at about 300, consists of the descendants of the few [[Punjabis]] who came during the [[Indian indenture system|indentureship period]] and [[Punjabi Sikhs]] who came in the twentieth and twenty-first century. The Sikhs have a [[gurdwara]] in [[Tunapuna]] dating back to 1929. There were also [[Punjabi Hindus]] and [[Punjabi Muslims]] who came during the indentured period as well in the twentieth and twenty-first century.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iOaR1gZ2A8Y | title=Sikh Channel in Trinidad - Episode 01 | website=[[YouTube]] | date=5 March 2019 }}</ref> [[Bhangra (music)|Bhangra]] has also had a minor impact on the local Indian [[Bhojpuri]]-derived [[chutney music]], with few songs mixing bhangra rhythms to create a ''chutney bhangra'' style.<ref>{{cite journal | jstor=853271 | title=Chutney and Indo-Trinidadian Cultural Identity | last1=Manuel | first1=Peter | journal=Popular Music | year=1998 | volume=17 | issue=1 | pages=21–43 | doi=10.1017/S0261143000000477 | s2cid=153586388 | url=https://academicworks.cuny.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1310&context=jj_pubs }}</ref>

old_content: [[Fiji Hindi]], also known as Fijian Baat or Fijian Hindustani, is the language spoken by most Fijian citizens of [[India]]n descent. It is derived mainly from the [[Awadhi]] and [[Bhojpuri language|Bhojpuri]] varieties of [[Hindi languages|Hindi]]. It has also borrowed a large number of words from [[Fijian language|Fijian]] and [[English language|English]]. The relation between Fiji Hindi and [[Standard Hindi]] is similar to the relation between [[Afrikaans]] and [[Dutch language|Dutch]]. Indian [[indenture]]d labourers were initially brought to Fiji mainly from districts of eastern [[Uttar Pradesh]], [[Bihar]], [[North-West Frontier (military history)|North-West Frontier]] and [[South India]] such as from [[Andhra Pradesh|Andhra]] and [[Tamil Nadu]]. They spoke numerous, mainly Hindi, dialects and languages depending on their district of origin.
