old_content: The Awards Ceremony, also known as the Closing Ceremony, takes place just before the end of a round. Traditionally, staff members stand on stage and announce the winners for the entire round. Winners either get a gold medal, silver medal, a pineapple (another form of trophy), or a trophy. The winner of the ''round'' gets the tallest trophy, and gets to interact with the props on the stage. Awards are also given to scholars who scored relatively well overall, but did not receive a gold medal or trophy for any particular event. These were initially called Da Vinci Awards, but their name was changed to the Asimov Award in 2023, as the award for the highest Challenge score, which was formerly named Asimov, had been renamed. Later, a [[Certificate of attendance|certificate]] will be shipped to all participants.<ref name=":1" />
new_content: The Awards Ceremony, also known as the Closing Ceremony, takes place just before the end of a round. Traditionally, staff members stand on stage and announce the winners for the entire round. Various winners may recieve gold medals, silver medals, trophies, or pineapples (Given with trophies). The winner of the ''round'' recieves the tallest trophy, and gets to interact with the props on the stage. These winners are given these awards for achievement in all events, both for team and individual recognition. Awards are also given to scholars who scored relatively well overall, but did not receive a gold medal or trophy for any particular event. These were initially called Da Vinci Awards, but their name was changed to the Asimov Award in 2023, as the award for the highest Challenge score, which was formerly named Asimov, had been renamed. Later, a [[Certificate of attendance|certificate]] will be shipped to all participants.<ref name=":1" />

old_content: In its simplest form, the term root system architecture (RSA) refers to the spatial configuration of a plant's root system. This system can be extremely complex and is dependent upon multiple factors such as the species of the plant itself, the composition of the soil and the availability of nutrients.<ref>{{cite journal| vauthors = Malamy JE |title=Intrinsic and environmental response pathways that regulate root system architecture |journal=Plant, Cell & Environment |year=2005|volume=28|issue=1 |pages=67–77 |doi=10.1111/j.1365-3040.2005.01306.x|pmid=16021787 |doi-access=free }}</ref> Root architecture plays the important role of providing a secure supply of nutrients and water as well as anchorage and support.
new_content: In its simplest form, the term root system architecture (RSA) refers to the spatial configuration of a plant's root system. In this article, RSA will be used as an acronym for root system architecture from now on. This system can be extremely complex and is dependent upon multiple factors such as the species of the plant itself, the composition of the soil and the availability of nutrients.<ref>{{cite journal| vauthors = Malamy JE |title=Intrinsic and environmental response pathways that regulate root system architecture |journal=Plant, Cell & Environment |year=2005|volume=28|issue=1 |pages=67–77 |doi=10.1111/j.1365-3040.2005.01306.x|pmid=16021787 |doi-access=free }}</ref> Root architecture plays the important role of providing a secure supply of nutrients and water as well as anchorage and support.

old_content: '''China–Switzerland relations''' officially began in 1918.<ref name="EDA">Yufang Zhou, Die Exterritorialitätsrechte der Schweiz in China (1918–1946), Frankfurt am Main und Bern 2003</ref> Economic relations between the two nations grew substantially in the 21st century, although relations have become somewhat strained since 2020 due to Swiss criticism of the [[Persecution of Uyghurs in China|China's persecution of the Uyghurs]] and the [[2020 Hong Kong national security law]].

old_content: '''The 2002 Waveney District Council election''' took place on 2 May 2002 to elect members of [[Waveney District|Waveney]] [[Non-metropolitan district|District]] Council in [[Suffolk]], [[England]]. The whole council was up for election with boundary changes since the [[2000 Waveney Council election|last election in 2000]].<ref name=lose>{{cite news| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/hi/english/static/vote2002/local_elections/159.stm | title = Waveney | access-date = 2010-11-30 | work = [[BBC News Online]]}}</ref> The [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour Party]] lost overall control of the council to [[no overall control]].<ref name=full>{{cite news | title = Full results | newspaper = [[Financial Times]] | page = 7 | date = 2002-05-03 }}</ref>

old_content: On January 25, Zwerner's attorney, Diane Toscano, stated that they intended to file a lawsuit regarding multiple failures by the administration to respond to concerns that the student had a gun on the school campus.<ref name=":10" /> Zwerner subsequently started litigation against the Newport News School Board and three former school district officials,<ref>{{Cite web |date=26 April 2023 |title=Newport News School Board's attorneys file motion to dismiss Abby Zwerner's lawsuit over Richneck shooting |url=https://www.13newsnow.com/article/news/education/newport-news-school-board-files-motion-to-dismiss-abby-zwerner-lawsuit-over-richneck-elementary-school-shooting/291-bddc88ab-a245-4b94-8f66-aa418eab1073 |access-date=2023-04-26 |website=13newsnow.com |language=en-US}}</ref> seeking damages of $40 million.<ref>{{Cite news|date=2023-04-03|title=Virginia teacher shot by a 6-year-old student files a $40 million lawsuit|author=AP|work=NPR|url=https://www.npr.org/2023/04/03/1167708211/virginia-teacher-abby-zwerner-richneck-newport-news-lawsuit|access-date=2023-04-04|archive-date=April 4, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230404143722/https://www.npr.org/2023/04/03/1167708211/virginia-teacher-abby-zwerner-richneck-newport-news-lawsuit|url-status=live}}</ref> In April 2023, lawyers for the school district filed a motion to dismiss Zwerner's lawsuit, which included claims that her injuries fell under the Virginian Worker's Compensation Act which allowed her to receive benefits but that she had rejected them in favor of the lawsuit.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Peterson |first=Beatrice |date=April 27, 2023 |title=District tries to dismiss lawsuit from teacher shot by 6-year-old, says it's covered under workers' comp |url=https://abcnews.go.com/US/district-dismiss-lawsuit-teacher-shot-6-year-covered/story?id=98921573 |access-date=2023-05-27 |website=ABC News |language=en}}</ref> A spokesperson for Newport News Public Schools said that Zwerner had resigned her position in March, and as a result her contract had expired on June 12 and was no longer employed old_content: The Chinese coast was first sighted around one month later. On 26 June 1731, ''Cron Printz Christian'' called at [[Macao]]. A delegation from the ship headed by van Hurk paid a visit to the Portuguese governor. On 27 June, a Chinese vessel escorted the delegation up the [[Pearl River]] to [[Canton]] to apply for permission from the [[Hoppo]] to send ''Cron Printz Christian'' up the Pearl River for trade. The permission reached the ship four days later. She was subsequently inspected both by Chinese customs officials and a Mandarin from the fort of [[Bocca Tigris]] before continuing up the river to anchorage of [[Whampoa anchorage|Whampoa]].
new_content: The Chinese coast was first sighted around one month later. On 26 June 1731, ''Cron Printz Christian'' called at [[Macao]]. A delegation from the ship headed by van Hurk paid a visit to the Portuguese governor. On 27 June, a Chinese vessel escorted the delegation up the [[Pearl River]] to [[Guangzhou|Canton]] to apply for permission from the [[Hoppo]] to send ''Cron Printz Christian'' up the Pearl River for trade. The permission reached the ship four days later. She was subsequently inspected both by Chinese customs officials and a Mandarin from the fort of [[Bocca Tigris]] before continuing up the river to anchorage of [[Whampoa anchorage|Whampoa]].

old_content: [[Rock art]] from the Upper Paleolithic, thought to represent a reindeer, was discovered on the back wall of Cathole Cave in September 2010. The engraving, measuring approximately 15 x 11 cm, has been radiocarbon dated to 14,505 ± 560 BP. According to George Nash, the archeologist who made the discovery, it is "the oldest rock art in the British Isles, if not north-western Europe".<ref name="NashonCathole">{{cite web |author=George Nash |title=2011 Nash on Cathole for Arkeos, Low res. |url=https://bristol.academia.edu/GeorgeNash/Papers/1269672/2011_Nash_on_Cathole_for_Arkeos_Low_res |access-date=4 June 2012 |publisher=[[Academia.edu]]|year=2011 |work=Academia.edu website}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-wales-south-west-wales-18648683 |title=Gower cave reindeer carving is Britain's oldest rock art |access-date=29 June 2012 |date=29 June 2012 |publisher=[[BBC]] |work=[[BBC News Online]] website}}</ref>

old_content: Goldberg-Polin was at the Supernova music festival when Hamas attacked the morning of 7 October. At around 8:00am, he sent his family a text message, "I love you". Ten minutes later he added, "I'm sorry."<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-10-23 |title=Young American-Israeli captive in Gaza is badly injured, father says |url=https://www.jpost.com/israel-news/defense-news/article-769699 |access-date=2023-11-16 |website=The Jerusalem Post}}</ref> During the attack, Goldberg-Polin, his best friend [[Aner Shapira]], and others took refuge in a field shelter. Hamas militants repeatedly threw grenades in the shelter.<ref name="captive">{{Cite news |date=17 October 2023 |title=Taken captive: Hersh Goldberg-Polin tied his own tourniquet |work=The Times of Israel |url=https://www.timesofisrael.com/taken-captive-hersh-goldberg-polin-tied-own-tourniquet-after-arm-blown-off/}}</ref>

old_content: [[File:Abbas and Amir Khan.png|thumb|Abbas and [[Aamir Khan]] in 2000]]
new_content: In 2000, Abbas appeared in a small role in Hey Ram, which starred [[Kamal Hassan]] along with Bollywood stars [[Shahrukh Khan]] and [[Rani Mukerji]] in the leading role. [[Dreams (2000 film)|Dreams]] a Malayalam film was released after Hey Ram, where Abbas appeared with [[Dileep]] and [[Meena (actress)|Meena]]. The movie became a flop at the box office. He then worked with [[Rajiv Menon]]'s romantic-drama [[Kandukondain Kandukondain|''Kandukondain Kandukondain'']] (2001), including an ensemble cast of [[Mammootty]], [[Ajith Kumar]], [[Aishwarya Rai Bachchan]] and Tabu.<ref name=":3">{{Cite web |date=2024-04-26 |title=South Actor Abbas' Family Photo Viral, Fans 'Wow' At Son's Striking Resemblance |url=https://www.news18.com/movies/south-actor-abbas-family-photo-viral-fans-wow-at-sons-striking-resemblance-8867361.html |access-date=2024-05-16 |website=News18 |language=en}}</ref> The film became commercially successful and marked the second collaboration of Abbas and Tabu after ''Kadhal Desam''.<ref name=":3" /> Abbas then acted in the Telugu film ''Madhuri'' which became a box-office failure.  [[File:Abbas and Amir Khan.png|thumb|Abbas and [[Aamir Khan]] in 2000]]

old_content: '''Somalia's Pidgin Italian'''(also called "Italian Somali Pidgin") is a language indigenous to [[Italian Somalia]]. It is the result of mixing [[Italian language|Italian]] with [[Somali language|Somalo]] and was used mainly in the first half of the 20th century in the area of [[:simple:Italian Mogadisco|Mogadishu]] (the Somalian capital).
new_content: '''Somalia's Pidgin Italian'''(also called "Italian Somali Pidgin") is a language indigenous to [[Italian Somalia]]. It is the result of mixing [[Italian language|Italian]] with [[Somali language|Somalo]] and was used mainly in the first half of the 20th century in the area of [[:simple:Italian Mogadiscio|Mogadishu]] (the Somalian capital).

old_content: '''Alperton''' is a [[London Underground]] station on the [[Uxbridge tube station|Uxbridge]] branch of the [[Piccadilly line]].<ref name=tubemap>{{cite map/Standard Tube Map}}</ref> The station is between [[Park Royal tube station|Park Royal]] and [[Sudbury Town tube station|Sudbury Town]] stations, in [[Travelcard Zone 4]].<ref name=tubemap /> It is located on Ealing Road (A4089), a short distance from the junction with Bridgewater Road ([[A4005 road|A4005]]), and is close to the [[Paddington]] branch of the [[Grand Union Canal]].
new_content: '''Alperton''' is a [[London Underground]] station in [[Alperton]], north-west [[London]]. It is on the [[Uxbridge tube station|Uxbridge]] branch of the [[Piccadilly line]] between [[Park Royal tube station|Park Royal]] and [[Sudbury Town tube station|Sudbury Town]] stations, in [[Travelcard Zone 4]].<ref name=tubemap>{{cite map/Standard Tube Map}}</ref><ref name=tubemap /> It is located on Ealing Road (A4089), a short distance from the junction with Bridgewater Road ([[A4005 road|A4005]]), and is close to the [[Paddington]] branch of the [[Grand Union Canal]].

old_content: In May 2020, it was announced that CJ Entertainment would be producing an English-language remake of the cult film with film-making duo [[Ari Aster]] and [[Lars Knudsen (producer)|Lars Knudsen]], whose credits include ''[[Midsommar (film)|Midsommar]]'' and ''[[Hereditary (film)|Hereditary]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/05/parasite-producer-cj-ari-aster-for-english-language-remake-of-cult-korean-movie-save-the-green-planet-1202927228/|title='Parasite' Producer CJ Teams With 'Midsommar' Duo & 'Succession' Scribe For English-Language Remake Of Cult Korean Movie 'Save The Green Planet!'|website=Deadline|date=7 May 2020|accessdate=7 May 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/save-green-planet-set-english-language-remake-1293742|title=Korean Cult Hit 'Save the Green Planet!' Set for Remake from CJ Entertainment, Ari Aster's Square Peg|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=7 May 2020}}</ref> In February 2024, it was reported that [[Yorgos Lanthimos]] was set to direct the remake, with Aster producing alongside Ed Guiney and Andrew Lowe from [[Element Pictures]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2024/film/news/yorgos-lanthimos-save-the-green-planet-remake-poor-things-element-pictures-1235911856/|title=Yorgos Lanthimos Sets Remake of Korean Fantasy Film ‘Save the Green Planet’ With ‘Poor Things’ Producer Element Pictures (EXCLUSIVE)|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=19 February 2024|accessdate=19 February 2024}}</ref>

Set for Remake from CJ Entertainment, Ari Aster's Square Peg|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=7 May 2020}}</ref> In February 2024, it was reported that [[Yorgos Lanthimos]] was set to direct the remake, with Aster producing alongside Ed Guiney and Andrew Lowe from [[Element Pictures]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2024/film/news/yorgos-lanthimos-save-the-green-planet-remake-poor-things-element-pictures-1235911856/|title=Yorgos Lanthimos Sets Remake of Korean Fantasy Film ‘Save the Green Planet’ With ‘Poor Things’ Producer Element Pictures (EXCLUSIVE)|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=19 February 2024|accessdate=19 February 2024}}</ref> In May 2024, [[Focus Features]] acquired all rights outside South Korea to the project, which had since been retitled to ''Bugonia''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Focus Features Takes Worldwide Rights To Yorgos Lanthimos’ Next Movie ‘Bugonia’ With Emma Stone & Jesse Plemons – Cannes|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|first1=Diana|last1=Lodderhose|first2=Anthony|last2=D'Alessandro|date=18 May 2024|access-date=18 May 2024|url=https://deadline.com/2024/05/bugonia-yorgos-lanthimos-emma-stone-movie-focus-features-1235917675/}}</ref>

old_content: Weygand returned to France in 1925 embittered, seeing his recall as the product of political machinations and intra-army rivalries. Regardless, he was awarded the [[Grand Cross of the Legion of Honor]] and promoted to [[général d'armée]].{{sfn|Clayton|2015|p=54}} Denied command in Morocco against the [[Rif War]] out of fear for his success, command in Syria since it would embarass the government, and command in Germany due to his closeness with Foch, he was made director of the ''Centre de Hautes Etudes Militaries'' (Center for Higher Military Studies) from 1925 to 1930.{{sfn|Clayton|2015|p=55, 56–57}} While Weygand supported development of a doctrine of rapid armoured assault with close air support, the government's view – which feared professionalisation of the army as a threat to regime stability and saw investment in tanks as financially ruinous – prevailed.{{sfn|Clayton|2015|pp=55–56 (noting the left-wing government's fear of a professional military and opposition to French military adventurism), 57–58 (noting Weygand's article in 1921 "in which he foresaw armoured divisions composed of fast tanks and self-propelled artillery... supported by aircraft strikes" as well as Weygand's doubts over tank speed and reliability in 1926)}}<ref>{{cite journal |last=Weygand |first=Maxime |title=La Cavalerie de la « Revue de Cavalerie » |year=1921 |volume=31 |issue=1 |journal=Revue de Cavalerie |pages=2–9 |quote=La guerre de demain sera plus encore que celle d'hier une guerre de machinisme... Que la cavalerie aille donc vers la machine, convaincue, par ailleurs, que celle-ci n'est pas pour la faire disparaître, mais pour lui donner un supplément de force |trans-quote=The war of tomorrow will be even more than that of yesterday a war of machinery... Let the cavalry therefore go towards the machine, convinced that this is not to end it, but to strengthen it }}</ref> The further programme to shorten conscripts' service was voted through in the late 1920s to Weygand's disapproval: he feared that the left was intending to replace the professional army with a purely defensive national guard while drowning units in basic training, making it impossible to train for large unit operations.{{sfn|Clayton|2015|p=58}} Settling at [[Morlaix]] in [[Brittany]] near Foch, the five years at the ''Centre'' also gave him time to write two books, biographies of French marshals Foch and [[Turenne]].{{sfn|Clayton|2015|pp=58–59}}

The Constitutional Court is charged with ruling on the conformity of laws and decrees with the constitution. old_content: During the 2024 WWE Hall of Fame induction ceremony on April 5th, he was honored by his family (who were there for the induction of his father Mike Rotunda, and his uncle Barry Windham, as part of the US Express) with the crowd showing his traditional "fireflies," and his music being played. The fireflies entrance would eventually be adopted by [[Jey Uso]], who [[Money in the Bank (2023)#Main event|withdrew]] from [[The Bloodline (professional wrestling)|The Bloodline]] to begin his [[Summerslam (2023)#Aftermath|singles run]] in late summer 2023, at the start of his match against [[Damian Priest]] at [[Backlash France]] the next month.<ref>https://tjrwrestling.net/news/jey-uso-makes-claims-ownership-wwe-fireflies/</ref>
new_content: During the 2024 WWE Hall of Fame induction ceremony on April 5th, he was honored by his family (who were there for the induction of his father Mike Rotunda, and his uncle Barry Windham, as part of the US Express) with the crowd showing his traditional "fireflies," and his music being played. old_content: At the beginning of the century, the German commander of the Navy [[Alfred von Tirpitz]] was building the [[High Seas Fleet]] with which he intended to challenge the supremacy of the [[Royal Navy]]. He focused on expensive [[battleship]]s and there was no role for submarines in his fleet. Only when Krupp exported its submarines to Russia, Italy, Norway and Austria-Hungary did Tirpitz order one submarine.{{Sfn|Blair||p=6}} The {{SMU|U-1|Germany|6}} was a completely redesigned {{sclass|Karp|submarine|1}} and when the [[Imperial German Navy]] commissioned it on 14 December 1906,{{Sfn|Showell||p=30}} it was the last major navy to possess submarines.{{Sfn|Blair||p=6}} The ''U-1'' had a double hull and a single torpedo tube. It used an [[electric motor]] powered by batteries for submerged propulsion and a [[Körting Hannover|Körting]] [[kerosene]] engine for charging the batteries and propulsion on the surface. The 50%-larger {{SMU|U-2|Germany|6}} (commissioned in 1908) had two torpedo tubes.
new_content: At the beginning of the century, the German commander of the Navy [[Alfred von Tirpitz]] was building the [[High Seas Fleet]] with which he intended to challenge the supremacy of the [[Royal Navy]]. He focused on expensive [[battleship]]s and there was no role for submarines in his fleet. Only when Krupp exported its submarines to Russia, Italy, Norway and Austria-Hungary did Tirpitz order one submarine.{{Sfn|Blair||p=6}} The {{SMU|U-1|Germany|6}} was a completely redesigned {{sclass|Karp|submarine|1}} and when the [[Imperial German Navy]] commissioned it on 14 December 1906,{{Sfn|Showell||p=30}} it was the last major navy to adopt submarines.{{Sfn|Blair||p=6}} The ''U-1'' had a double hull and a single torpedo tube. It used an [[electric motor]] powered by batteries for submerged propulsion and a [[Körting Hannover|Körting]] [[kerosene]] engine for charging the batteries and propulsion on the surface. The 50%-larger {{SMU|U-2|Germany|6}} (commissioned in 1908) had two torpedo tubes.

old_content: "Butterfly" contains two verses, a bridge, and a chorus that repeats four times.<ref name="Booklet"/> It uses flying as a freedom metaphor and materializes this via the [[butterfly]], "a delicate symbol of beauty" according to [[Neil Strauss]] of ''[[The New York Times]]''.<ref name="Strauss"/> Critics viewed the song as having a positive<ref name="Strauss">{{cite news|last=Strauss|first=Neil|author-link=Neil|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1997/11/12/arts/critic-s-notebook-in-the-pop-kingdom-flying-is-the-reigning-metaphor.html|url-access=limited|title=Flying Is the Reigning Metaphor|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|date=September 21, 1997|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230318031344/https://www.nytimes.com/1997/11/12/arts/critic-s-notebook-in-the-pop-kingdom-flying-is-the-reigning-metaphor.html|archive-date=March 18, 2023}}</ref><ref name="Pareles">{{cite news|last=Pareles|first=Jon|author-link=Jon Pareles|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1997/09/21/arts/recordings-view-a-new-gentleness-from-a-pop-diva.html|url-access=limited|title=A New Gentleness from a Pop Diva|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|date=September 21, 1997|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221121083434/https://www.nytimes.com/1997/09/21/arts/recordings-view-a-new-gentleness-from-a-pop-diva.html|archive-date=November 21, 2022}}</ref> and inspirational tone.{{efn-ua|Such as Jon O'Brien of ''Billboard'',<ref name="O'Brien"/> Kevin O'Hare of the ''[[Sunday Republican]]'',<ref name="O'Hare">{{cite news|last=O'Hare|first=Kevin|date=September 18, 1997|title=Diva-luation|newspaper=[[Cincinnati Post]]|agency=[[Newhouse News Service]]|department=Time Out|page=11|url=https://www.newspapers.com/article/the-cincinnati-post/146040569/|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|archive-date=April 25, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240425194652/https://www.newspapers.com/article/the-cincinnati-post/146040569/|url-status=live}}</ref> and Melissa Ruggieri of the ''[[Richmond Times-Dispatch]]''<ref name="Ruggieri">{{cite news|last=Ruggieri|first=Melissa|date=September 16, 1997|title=Independence|newspaper=[[Richmond Times-Dispatch]]|page=D1|url=https://www.newspapers.com/article/richmond-times-dispatch/146040250/|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|archive-date=April 25, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240425194724/https://www.newspapers.com/article/richmond-times-dispatch/146040250/|url-status=live}}</ref>}} For ''Billboard''{{'}}s Samantha Xu and ''[[The Plain Dealer]]''{{'}}s John Soeder, "Butterfly" emotionally processes the act of adapting in life.<ref name="Soeder"/><ref name="Xu">{{cite magazine|last=Xu|first=Samantha|display-authors=etal|url=https://www.billboard.com/media/lists/mariah-carey-greatest-songs-top-100-9460564/|title=The 100 Greatest Mariah Carey Songs: Staff Picks|date=October 5, 2020|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220519172808/https://www.billboard.com/media/lists/mariah-carey-greatest-songs-top-100-9460564/|archive-date=May 19, 2022}}</ref> Newfound personal autonomy was viewed as a major lyrical theme;{{efn-ua|By those from ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'',<ref name="Verna">{{cite magazine|title=Singles|editor-last=Verna|editor-first=Paul|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|page=74|date=September 13, 1997|id={{ProQuest|227095770}}}}</ref> Connie Johnson of the ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'',<ref name="Johnson"/> and Anthony Violanti of the ''[[Buffalo News]]'',<ref name="Violanti">{{cite news|last=Violanti|first=Anthony|date=September 16, 1997|title=Mariah Carey Emerges from Her Musical Cocoon|newspaper=[[Buffalo News]]|page=C1|url=https://www.newspapers.com/article/the-buffalo-news/146040179/|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|archive-date=May 1, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240501063042/https://www.newspapers.com/article/the-buffalo-news/146040179/|url-status=live}}</ref> among others}} Lindsey Dobbins dubbed it the "Mariah Carey Declaration of Independence" in ''[[Vulture (website)|Vulture]]''.<ref name="Dobbins">{{cite news|last1=Weber|first1=Lindsey|last2=Dobbins|first2=Amanada|url=https://www.vulture.com/2014/05/these-are-mariah-careys-25-best-singles.html|title=These Are Mariah Carey's 25 Best Singles|work=[[Vulture (website)|Vulture]]|date=May 28, 2014|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231108220246/https://www.vulture.com/2014/05/these-are-mariah-careys-25-best-singles.html|archive-date=November 8, 2023}}</ref> ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]''{{'}}s [[David Browne (journalist)|David Browne]] and the ''[[Gavin Report]]''{{'}}s Annette M. Lai said it utilizes the adage of loving someone enough to let them go.<ref name="Browne"/><ref name="Lai">{{cite magazine|last=Lai|first=Annette M.|title=A/C Picks|date=September 26, 1997|magazine=[[Gavin Report]]|page=62}}</ref> More specifically, others deemed it a derivative of the 1985 [[Sting (musician)|Sting]] song "[[If You Love Somebody Set Them Free]]".{{efn-ua|Attributed to Michael Corcoran of the ''[[Austin American-Statesman]]'',<ref name="Corcoran">{{cite news|last=Corcoran|first=Michael|date=September 16, 1997|title=Mariah Carey Takes Flight on ''Butterfly''|newspaper=[[Austin American-Statesman]]|pages=E1, E3|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/113410572/austin-american-statesman/|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|archive-date=November 21, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221121083435/https://www.newspapers.com/clip/113410572/austin-american-statesman/|url-status=live}}</ref> Timothy Finn of the ''[[Kansas City Star]]'',<ref name="Finn">{{cite news|last=Finn|first=Timothy|date=September 22, 1997|title=Singing for Her Suffering|newspaper=[[Kansas City Star]]|page=E8|url=https://www.newspapers.com/article/the-kansas-city-star/146041539/|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|archive-date=April 25, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240425194735/https://www.newspapers.com/article/the-kansas-city-star/146041539/|url-status=live}}</ref> and John Soeder of ''[[The Plain Dealer]]''<ref name="Soeder"/>}}

old_content: Richneck Elementary School remained closed during the subsequent week.<ref name=":4">{{Cite news |date=2023-01-09 |title=Abby Zwerner: US school where six-year-old shot teacher shut all week |language=en-GB |work=BBC News |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-64210387 |url-status=live |access-date=2023-01-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230124044613/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-64210387 |archive-date=January 24, 2023}}</ref> The school announced that Principal Briana Foster Newton had left the position shortly before the school re-opened on January 30. old_content: DiMaggio enjoyed a close friendship with teammates [[Ted Williams]], [[Bobby Doerr]], and [[Johnny Pesky]], which was chronicled in [[David Halberstam]]'s book ''The Teammates''. After retiring, he became a plastics manufacturer in New England. DiMaggio was inducted into the [[Boston Red Sox Hall of Fame]] in {{Baseball year|1995}}. He and his wife Emily, whom he married in 1948, had two sons (Paul and Peter), a daughter (Emily), and several grandchildren (Alex, Andrew, Charlotte, Margel, Peter, and Anna).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kansascity.com/485/story/1185521.html|title=Red Sox great Dom DiMaggio dies}}</ref>

old_content: '''Weinstein''' is a German or [[Yiddish]] surname meaning [[:de:Weinstein|wine stone]], referring to the crystals of [[potassium bitartrate|cream of tartar (potassium bitartrate)]] resulting from the process of [[winemaking|fermenting grape juice]].<ref>[https://www.hermeswein.de/content/73-weinstein-mineralkristalle-des-weins “Weinstein - Kristalle des Weins (Tartar: Crystals of Wine)”], Hermeswein website.</ref>

old_content: Mwedihanga began his soccer career playing for Teenagers Football club in [[Ongwediva]].  He then moved to [[United Africa Tigers]], where he made a name for himself as a no nonsense centre back. In 2012, he joined [[AmaZulu F.C.|Amazulu FC]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Son of the soil shines across border {{!}} Namibia Economist |url=https://economist.com.na/9012/sport/son-of-the-soil-shines-across-border/ |access-date=2024-05-18 |language=en-GB}}</ref> He later left [[AmaZulu F.C.|Amazulu FC]] at the end of 2014/2015 season after they got relegated and joined [[University of Pretoria]]. In 2015, he led Namibia to their 1st international Cup [[COSAFA]] Cup conceding only one goal in over 3 matches.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2016-05-09 |title=How Namibia won the 2015 COSAFA Castle Cup |url=https://cosafa.com/how-namibia-won-the-2015-cosafa-castle-cup/ |access-date=2024-05-18 |language=en-GB}}</ref>

old_content: One of his works took the title from the last work of [[Alexander Anderson (mathematician)|Alexander Anderson]], published in 1619 in Paris: ''Alexandri Andersoni Exercitationum Mathematicarum Decas Prima''.<ref>Cajori :[https://www.archive.org/stream/williamoughtredg00cajouoft#page/66/mode/2up/search/Naples William Oughtred, a great seventeenth-century teacher of mathematics]</ref>
new_content: One of his works took the title from the last work of [[Alexander Anderson (mathematician)|Alexander Anderson]], published in 1619 in Paris: ''Alexandri Andersoni Exercitationum Mathematicarum Decas Prima''.<ref>Cajori :[https://www.archive.org/stream/williamoughtredg00cajouoft#page/66/mode/2up/search/Naples William Oughtred, a great seventeenth-century teacher of mathematics]</ref> This work shows that Glorioso wrote his [[Algebra|algebrical]] calculations in a language inherited from the algebra of Viète.<ref>Joseph Frederick Scott : [https://books.google.com/books?id=XX9PKytw8g8C&q=Cataldus+%22Vieta%22Themathematical&pg=PA148 work of John Wallis, D.D., F.R.S., (1616-1703) ]</ref> It's one of the first work to use the notation <math>Aqqc</math> for the equivalent of the current <math>A^{8}</math>.

old_content: Maryam Umar Maigida, (29-year-old) is a visual artist, freelance painter, and art historian. She has a bachelor's degree in fine arts from Ahmadu Bello University. She is also known as the owner of the art cave studio and gallery "Her studio." She has participated in a number of exhibitions in Nigeria, the majority of which were in Apex Arts in New York, Obsidian Group Exhibition Black History in London, and World Arts because she paints in a variety of styles, including abstract, near naturalism, and mixed media. With a focus on culturally relevant fabrics, motifs, and materials as a means of preserving culture, and with some of her work advocating for women's rights, children's rights, and preventing child abuse<ref>{{Cite web |last=Nigeria |first=Guardian |date=2023-06-25 |title=Maryam Maigida: The Artist Breaking Stereotypes |url=https://guardian.ng/life/maryam-maigida-the-artist-breaking-stereotypes/ |access-date=2024-05-18 |website=The Guardian Nigeria News - Nigeria and World News |language=en-US}}</ref>
new_content: [[Maryam Umar Maigida]] (29-year-old) is a [[Nigerian]] [[Visual arts|visual artist]], freelance [[painter]], and art historian. And has a bachelor's degree in [[Fine art|fine arts]] from [[Ahmadu Bello University]]. She is also known as the owner of the art cave studio and gallery "Her studio." She has participated in a number of [[Exhibition|exhibitions]] in Nigeria, the majority of which were in [[Apexart|Apex Arts]] in New York, Obsidian Group Exhibition Black History in London, and World Arts Dubai UAE, Her paints are seen in variety of styles, including abstract, near naturalism, and mixed media. With a focus on culturally relevant fabrics, motifs, and materials as a means of preserving culture, also, some of her work advocating for women's rights, children's rights, and preventing child abuse

old_content: '''William Howard Adams''' (1926 – July 5, 2023)is an author, curator and lecturer on history and garden design. He is a senior fellow at the [[Dumbarton Oaks|Dumbarton Oaks Research Library]] in Washington, D.C. and a Fellow of the International Center for Jefferson Studies. His house, [[Hazelfield]], in [[Shenandoah Junction, West Virginia]] is listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]].

old_content: Religion in ancient Armenia was historically related to a set of beliefs that, in Persia, led to the emergence of [[Zoroastrianism]]. It particularly focused on the worship of [[Mithra]] and also included a pantheon of gods such as [[Aramazd]], [[Vahagn]], [[Anahit]], and [[Astghik]]. The country used the solar [[Armenian calendar]], which consisted of 12 months.<ref name="j409">{{cite book | last=Melton | first=J.G. | last2=Baumann | first2=M. | title=Religions of the World: A Comprehensive Encyclopedia of Beliefs and Practices [6 volumes] | publisher=Bloomsbury Publishing | year=2010 | isbn=978-1-59884-204-3 | url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=qejaEAAAQBAJ&pg=PA470 | access-date=May 11, 2024 | page=470}}</ref>
new_content: Religion in ancient Armenia was historically related to a set of beliefs that, in Persia, led to the emergence of [[Zoroastrianism]]. It particularly focused on the worship of [[Mithra]] and also included a pantheon of gods such as [[Aramazd]], [[Vahagn]], [[Anahit]], and [[Astghik]]. The country used the solar [[Armenian calendar]], which consisted of 12 months.<ref name="j409">{{cite book | last1=Melton | first1=J.G. | last2=Baumann | first2=M. | title=Religions of the World: A Comprehensive Encyclopedia of Beliefs and Practices [6 volumes] | publisher=Bloomsbury Publishing | year=2010 | isbn=978-1-59884-204-3 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=qejaEAAAQBAJ&pg=PA470 | access-date=May 11, 2024 | page=470}}</ref>

new_content: Hogmanay would not be featured in a BBC New Year's special broadcast outside of Scotland again until 1998–99, when BBC One aired ''New Year Live—''an equally-shambolic adaptation of BBC Scotland's ''[[BBC Scotland's Hogmanay|Hogmanay Live]]'' format presented by [[Carol Smillie]] and [[Fred MacAulay]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=McCann |first=Graham |date=2023-12-31 |title=Hogmanay Hell: The BBC's New Year Live 98 - Comedy Chronicles |url=https://www.comedy.co.uk/features/comedy_chronicles/hogmanay-hell-new-year-live-98/ |access-date=2024-04-22 |website=British Comedy Guide |language=en}}</ref> Marking the occasion, a [[Mark Lamarr]] documentary on ''Live into 85'' would air on [[BBC Two]] as part of its New Year's Eve lineup.<ref name=":2" />

old_content: Following the approval of the ''[[Voyager program|Voyager]]'' missions, NASA's Scientific Advisory Group for Outer Solar System Missions considered the requirements for Jupiter orbiters and atmospheric probes. It noted that the technology to build a [[heat shield]] for an atmospheric probe did not yet exist, and indeed facilities to test one under the conditions found on Jupiter would not be available until 1980. There was also concern about the effects of radiation on spacecraft components, which would be better understood after ''Pioneer 10'' and ''Pioneer 11'' had conducted their flybys. ''Pioneer 10''{{'}}s flyby in December 1973 indicated that the effects were not as severe as had been feared.{{sfn|Meltzer|2007|pp=29–30}} NASA management designated JPL as the lead center for the Jupiter Orbiter Probe (JOP) Project.{{sfn|Meltzer|2007|pp=32–33}} [[John R. Casani]], who had headed the ''[[Mariner program|Mariner]]'' and ''Voyager'' projects, became the first project manager.<ref>{{cite web |publisher= NASA  |title=NASA's 50 Year Men and Women |url=https://www.nasa.gov/50th/50th_magazine/50yearsEmployees.html |access-date=October 28, 2020}}</ref> The JOP would be the fifth spacecraft to visit Jupiter, but the first to orbit it, and the probe the first to enter its atmosphere.{{sfn|Dawson|Bowles|2004|pp=190–191}}
new_content: Following the approval of the ''[[Voyager program|Voyager]]'' missions, NASA's Scientific Advisory Group for Outer Solar System Missions considered the requirements for Jupiter orbiters and atmospheric probes. There was also concern about the effects of radiation on spacecraft components, which would be better understood after ''Pioneer 10'' and ''Pioneer 11'' had conducted their flybys. ''Pioneer 10''{{'}}s flyby in December 1973 indicated that the effects were not as severe as had been feared.{{sfn|Meltzer|2007|pp=29–30}} NASA management designated JPL as the lead center for the Jupiter Orbiter Probe (JOP) Project.{{sfn|Meltzer|2007|pp=32–33}} [[John R. Casani]], who had headed the ''[[Mariner program|Mariner]]'' and ''Voyager'' projects, became the first project manager.<ref>{{cite web |publisher=NASA |title=NASA's 50 Year Men and Women |url=https://www.nasa.gov/50th/50th_magazine/50yearsEmployees.html |access-date=October 28, 2020 |archive-date=March 19, 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100319002842/https://www.nasa.gov/50th/50th_magazine/50yearsEmployees.html |url-status=dead }}</ref> The JOP would be the fifth spacecraft to visit Jupiter, but the first to orbit it, and the probe the first to enter its atmosphere.{{sfn|Dawson|Bowles|2004|pp=190–191}}

old_content: There is a widespread false belief that Kennedy made an embarrassing mistake by saying ''Ich bin '''ein''' Berliner''.  By including the [[indefinite article]] "ein," he supposedly changed the meaning of the sentence from the intended "I am a citizen of Berlin" to "I am a [[Berliner (doughnut)|Berliner]]" (a Berliner being a type of German pastry, similar to a jam- or jelly-filled doughnut), amusing Germans throughout the city. However, this is incorrect from both a grammatical perspective and a historical perspective.
new_content: There is a widespread false belief that Kennedy made an mistake by saying ''Ich bin '''ein''' Berliner''.  By including the [[indefinite article]] "ein," he supposedly changed the meaning of the sentence from the intended "I am a citizen of Berlin" to "I am a [[Berliner (doughnut)|Berliner]]" (a Berliner being a type of German pastry, similar to a jam- or jelly-filled doughnut), amusing Germans throughout the city. However, this is incorrect from both a grammatical perspective and a historical perspective.
|50 Million Years Ago

old_content: ''The Artistry of Mark Murphy''  is the YYth [[studio album]] by American jazz vocalist Mark Murphy. It was recorded in 1982 when Murphy was 50 years old and released by the [[Muse Records|Muse]] label in the United States in MMMM. The album is a collection .
new_content: ''The Artistry of Mark Murphy''  is the 19th [[studio album]] by American jazz vocalist Mark Murphy. It was recorded in 1982 when Murphy was 50 years old and released by the [[Muse Records|Muse]] label in the United States in MMMM. The album is a collection of jazz tunes and standards. Murphy contributes original lyrics to [[George Wallington]]'s "Godchild".

old_content: In April 2024, a grand jury charged the school's former assistant principal, Ebony Parker, with eight counts of felony child neglect. old_content: According to the [[U.S. Geological Survey]], a total of 227,898 people died.<ref name="usgs"/> Measured in lives lost, this is one of the ten [[Lists of earthquakes#Deadliest earthquakes|worst earthquakes in recorded history]], as well as the single worst tsunami in history. Indonesia was the worst affected area, with most death toll estimates at around 170,000.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.islamicreliefusa.org/home?aspxerrorpath=/404.aspx |title=Home |publisher=Islamic Relief USA |access-date=12 August 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110119163003/http://www.islamicreliefusa.org/home?aspxerrorpath=/404.aspx |archive-date=19 January 2011 |url-status = live }}</ref> An initial report by [[Siti Fadilah Supari]], the Indonesian Minister of Health at the time, estimated the death total to be as high as 220,000 in Indonesia alone, giving a total of 280,000 fatalities.<ref name=BBC280>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/asia-pacific/4204385.stm|title=Indonesia quake toll jumps again|work=BBC News|date=25 January 2005|access-date=24 December 2012|archive-date=21 August 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210821153214/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/4204385.stm|url-status=live}}</ref> However, the estimated number of dead and missing in Indonesia were later reduced by over 50,000. In their report, the [[Tsunami Evaluation Coalition]] stated, "It should be remembered that all such data are subject to error, as data on missing persons especially are not always as good as one might wish".<ref>{{Cite report |url=https://cdn.sida.se/publications/files/sida61330en-joint-evaluation-of-the-international-response-to-the-indian-ocean-tsunami.pdf |title=Joint Evaluation of the International Response to the Indian Ocean Tsunami: Synthesis Report |last=Telford |first=John |last2=Cosgrave |first2=John |date=2006 |publisher=Tsunami Evaluation Coalition |page=159 |language=en |access-date=18 May 2024 |ISBN=0-85003-807-3}}</ref> A much higher number of deaths has been suggested for Myanmar based on reports from Thailand.<ref name="AsiaNews-Myanmar"/> The death toll for Indonesia alone may be as high as 172,761 lives.<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Parwanto |first=Novia Budi |last2=Oyama |first2=Tatsuo |date=2014 |title=A statistical analysis and comparison of historical earthquake and tsunami disasters in Japan and Indonesia |url=https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ijdrr.2013.10.003 |journal=International Journal of Disaster Risk Reduction |volume=7 |pages=122–141 |doi=10.1016/j.ijdrr.2013.10.003 |issn=2212-4209}}</ref>

old_content: Roy Campanella was born in Philadelphia to parents Ida, who was [[African Americans|African American]], and John Campanella, son of [[Italian-Americans|Italian immigrants]]. Roy was the youngest of the four children born to the couple. They first lived in [[Germantown, Philadelphia|Germantown]], and then moved to [[Nicetown]] in [[North Philadelphia]], where the children attended integrated schools.<ref>'' Jackie & Campy'' by William C. Kashatus, pp. 44</ref>
new_content: Roy Campanella was born in Philadelphia on November 19 1921 to parents Ida, who was [[African Americans|African American]], and John Campanella, son of [[Italian-Americans|Italian immigrants]]. Roy was the youngest of the four children born to the couple. They first lived in [[Germantown, Philadelphia|Germantown]], and then moved to [[Nicetown]] in [[North Philadelphia]], where the children attended integrated schools.<ref>'' Jackie & Campy'' by William C. old_content: '''Sir Anthony Joseph Francis O'Reilly''' {{post-nominals|country=GBR|size=100%|AO}} ( 7 May 1936 – 18 May 2024) was an Irish former businessman and international [[rugby union]] player. He was known for his involvement in the [[Independent News & Media Group]], which he led from 1973 to 2009,<ref name="DepartsINM">Dublin, Ireland, The Irish Times, Friday 13 May (quoted at [http://news.eircom.net/breakingnews/general/15165361/ eircom.net] also), and Saturday 14 May 2009 {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090314070355/http://news.eircom.net/breakingnews/general/15165361/ |date=14 March 2009 }}</ref> and as former [[CEO]] and chairman of the [[H.J. Heinz Company]]. He was the leading shareholder of [[Waterford Wedgwood]]. As of 26 May 2014, O'Reilly was being pursued in the Irish courts for debts amounting to €22 million by [[Allied Irish Banks|AIB]], following losses amounting to hundreds of millions of euros in his unsuccessful attempt to stop [[Denis O'Brien]] from assuming control of [[Independent News & Media]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rte.ie/news/2014/0526/619683-aib-oreilly/|title=AIB case against O'Reilly for Commercial Court|date=26 May 2014|work=RTÉ.ie|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140527215821/http://www.rte.ie/news/2014/0526/619683-aib-oreilly/|archive-date=27 May 2014}}</ref>

old_content: The '''Trinitatiskirche''', or '''St. Trinitatis''' (Holy [[Trinity]]) in [[Wolfenbüttel]], Lower Saxony, Germany, is a Baroque [[Lutheran]] church consecrated in 1719. It is the seat of the bishop of the [[Evangelical Lutheran Church in Brunswick|Lutheran Church in Brunswick]] and also serves as a concert venue.
new_content: The '''Trinitatiskirche''', or '''St. Trinitatis''' (Holy [[Trinity]]) in [[Wolfenbüttel]], Lower Saxony, Germany, is a Baroque [[Lutheran]] church consecrated in 1719. It is a rare Baroque church in Lower Saxony, that also serves as a concert venue.

old_content: The name of the city of Osh derives from the river [[Vakhsh (river)|Vakhsh]], anthropomorphised there as a water goddess of the same name, who was worshipped (in tandem with Atash, the sacred fire) in a Zoroastrian shrine or fire temple situated in the Eagle Cave in the ancient sacred mountain [[Sulayman Mountain|Sulaiman-Too]]. The river Vakhsh itself, known also as Surkhob  or Kyzyl-Suu ( Turkic: “red water”) is a tributary of the Amu Darya, the course of the Vakhsh lying to the South of the Fergana valley, rising as it does near the village of [[Sary-Tash]] and flowing southwest to join the Amu Darya not far from [[Panj]].<ref>A little history of the city of Osh https://osh-hospital.narod.ru/history_osh.htm; Live the East. info@centralasia-travel.com; Retrieved 17/4/2024.</ref>
new_content: The name of the city of Osh derives from the river [[Vakhsh (river)|Vakhsh]], anthropomorphised there as a water goddess of the same name, who was worshipped (in tandem with [[Atar]], sacred fire) in a Zoroastrian shrine or fire temple situated in the Eagle Cave in the ancient sacred mountain [[Sulayman Mountain|Sulaiman-Too]]. The river Vakhsh itself, known also as Surkhob  or Kyzyl-Suu ( Turkic: “red water”) is a tributary of the Amu Darya, the course of the Vakhsh lying to the South of the Fergana valley, rising as it does near the village of [[Sary-Tash]] and flowing southwest to join the Amu Darya not far from [[Panj]].<ref>A little history of the city of Osh https://osh-hospital.narod.ru/history_osh.htm; Live the East. info@centralasia-travel.com; Retrieved 17/4/2024.</ref>

old_content: By 2020, fourteen of the [[Constitutional Tribunal (Poland)|Constitutional Tribunal]]'s fifteen judges had been appointed by the [[Sejm]] since the 2015 return of [[Law and Justice (Poland)|Law and Justice]] to power. Its domination over all branches of power has created [[2015 Polish Constitutional Court crisis|a political crisis]] that has led the [[European Commission]] to refer Poland to the [[European Court of Justice]].<ref name="CE_20171220">{{cite web|publisher=European Commission| title =Rule of Law: European Commission acts to defend judicial independence in Poland| date =2017-12-20| url =http://europa.eu/rapid/press-release_IP-17-5367_en.htm| access-date =2018-02-11| archive-url =https://www.webcitation.org/6x8fb1HDp?url=http://europa.eu/rapid/press-release_IP-17-5367_en.htm| archive-date =2018-02-11| url-status =live}}</ref>

old_content: ''Combat'' uses two four-directional [[joystick]]s, one for each player.{{sfn|Montfort|Bogost|2009|p=22}} The game has several modes of gameplay: "[[Tank]]", "[[Biplane]]" and "[[Jet aircraft|Jet]]" and with variations of the above models.{{sfn|Montfort|Bogost|2009|p=19}} The tank and jet modes are viewed from a top-down perspective while biplane games are side view.{{sfn|Weiss}} In all forms of the game, pushing the button fires a missile. Hitting the other player with a missile scores a point. The player with the most points at the end of a two minutes and sixteen second round wins. Variations of the gameplay in Tank mode include adding obstacles to maneuver around, having the missiles rebound off of walls (referred to as Tank-Pong) and a mode where the tanks are invisible except when they are firing a missile or are hit by one.{{sfn|Montfort|Bogost|2009|p=19}}{{sfn|Montfort|Bogost|2009|p=31}} In the other two modes, Jet and Biplane, there are no obstacles, and both aircraft continuously move forward.{{sfn|Montfort|Bogost|2009|p=19}} These levels have options for obscuring clouds that the planes can hide behind.{{sfn|Montfort|Bogost|2009|p=31}} The original Atari VCS game system has six switches in front, including left and right difficulty switches and a game select switch. The difficulty switches change the range of fire of the missiles and in the plane-based games also changes the speed of flight.{{sfn|Montfort|2006}}
new_content: ''Combat'' uses two four-directional [[joystick]]s, one for each player.{{sfn|Montfort|Bogost|2009|p=22}} The game has several modes of gameplay: "[[Tank]]", "[[Biplane]]" and "[[Jet aircraft|Jet]]" and with variations of the above models.{{sfn|Montfort|Bogost|2009|p=19}} The tank and jet modes are viewed from a top-down perspective while biplane games are side view.{{sfn|Weiss}} In all forms of the game, pushing the button fires a missile. Hitting the other player with a missile scores a point. The player with the most points at the end of a two minutes and sixteen second round wins. Variations of the gameplay in Tank mode include adding obstacles to maneuver around, having the missiles rebound off of walls (referred to as Tank-Pong) and a mode where the tanks are invisible except when they are firing a missile or are hit by one.{{sfn|Montfort|Bogost|2009|p=19}}{{sfn|Montfort|Bogost|2009|p=31}} In the other two modes, Jet and Biplane, there are no obstacles, and both aircraft continuously move forward.{{sfn|Montfort|Bogost|2009|p=19}} These levels have options for obscuring clouds that the planes can hide behind.{{sfn|Montfort|Bogost|2009|p=31}} The original 1977 Atari VCS (Video Computer System) has six switches in front, including left and right difficulty switches and a game select switch. The difficulty switches change the range of fire of the missiles and in the plane-based games also changes the speed of flight.{{sfn|Montfort|2006}}

old_content: The mosque has 6 entrances and 2 side entrances to the ladies' chapel on the first floor, The 6 entrances are located on the facade of the mosques with pishtaqs in front of them with the central entrance being slightly bigger than the ones on each side. The middle entrance has 3 horse shoe arches supported by 4 engaged columns while the smaller entrances has 2 horseshoe arches supported by 3 engaged columns. The side entrances each have a small, white dome on top of them while the middle entrance does not. The middle entrances has writings on the outside wall with the name of the mosque written in Arabic in Kufic style.

Now ostracized, Timon decides to leave. He meets the mandrill [[Rafiki (The Lion King)|Rafiki]], who teaches him about "Hakuna Matata", and advises him to "look beyond what you see". Timon takes this advice literally and observes Pride Rock in the distance. Believing Pride Rock to be his dream home, Timon ventures in that direction and encounters Pumbaa the [[warthog]] on his way. The two quickly form a bond, and Pumbaa accompanies Timon on his journey.
new_content: In a dark theater, Timon and Pumbaa watches the opening act of [[The Lion King]] until Timon uses a remote to fast forward to Hakuna Matata scene. Pumbaa tries to rewind the film back to the beginning but Timon tries to fast forward causing them to fight over the remotes. Timon eventually decided to tell the story about how they met and learn Hakuna Matata. Pumbaa agreeds with his idea as Timon rewinds the film to before the beginning where the story begins.

old_content: As designed, the ''Daring''-class ships had a standard displacement of 2,950 tons, with a full load displacement of 3,580 tons.<ref name=McCart219/> Length was {{convert|390|ft}} overall and {{convert|366|ft}} between perpendiculars, with a beam of {{convert|43|ft}} and a maximum draught of {{convert|17|ft}}.<ref name=McCart219/> Propulsion machinery consisted of two oil-fuelled boilers (for ''Duchess'', these were supplied by [[Forster Wheeler]]), connected to [[Parsons geared turbine|Parsons double reduction geared turbines]] from [[English Electric]], which supplied {{convert|54,000|shp}} to the ship's two propeller shafts.<ref name=McCart219/> Top speed was {{convert|30.5|kn}}, with an effective range of {{convert|1,700|nmi}}, while a cruising speed of {{convert|20|kn}} allowed the ship to cover {{convert|4,400|nmi}}.<ref name=McCart219/> ''Duchess'', along with three of her sister ships, were fitted with [[alternating current]] internal electrics; a break from Royal Navy practice.<ref name=McCartIX/> The intended ship's company for ''Duchess'' was 278.<ref name=McCart219/>

old_content: [[File:English_Grammar_Time_Simple_Present.png|thumb|Presentism is seen as a Heraclitean view.|200x200px]]The [[British idealism|British idealist]] [[J. M. E. McTaggart]] is best known for his paper "[[The Unreality of Time]]" (1908), in which he argues that time is unreal. His "[[A series and B series#A series|A series]]", also known as [[Philosophical presentism|presentism]] or "temporal becoming", which conceptualizes of time as tensed (''i.e.'', having the properties of being past, present, or future), has been described as Heraclitean. By contrast, his " "[[B-theory of time|B-theory]]", under which time is tenseless (''i.e.'', earlier than, simultaneous to, or later than), has been associated with Parmenides.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Markosian |first1=Ned |author-link=Ned Markosian |title=Time |url=http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/time/#PreEteGroUniThe |access-date=28 December 2014 |publisher=Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy}}</ref><ref>Craig, William Lane (1999). Temporal Becoming and the Direction of Time. Philosophy and Theology 11 (2):349-366.</ref><ref>see [https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/spacetime-bebecome Being and Becoming in Modern Physics ]</ref> Advocates of presentism include [[Arthur Prior]] and [[William Lane Craig]].

By contrast, his " "[[B-theory of time|B-theory]]", under which time is tenseless (''i.e.'', earlier than, simultaneous to, or later than), has been associated with Parmenides.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Markosian |first1=Ned |author-link=Ned Markosian |title=Time |url=http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/time/#PreEteGroUniThe |access-date=28 December 2014 |publisher=Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy}}</ref><ref>Craig, William Lane (1999). Temporal Becoming and the Direction of Time. Philosophy and Theology 11 (2):349-366.</ref><ref>see [https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/spacetime-bebecome Being and Becoming in Modern Physics ]</ref> Advocates of presentism include [[Arthur Prior]] and [[William Lane Craig]].

new_content: Bengali cinema enjoyed a large, even disproportionate, representation in Indian cinema during this period. They produced directors like [[Satyajit Ray]],[[Mrinal Sen]],[[Tapan Sinha]] and The revival in Bengali Mainstream cinema dates from the rise of directors such as  [[Tarun Majumdar]] along with [[Arabinda Mukhopadhyay]].[[ Satyajit Ray]] who was an [[Academy Honorary Award]] winner, and the recipient of India's and France's greatest civilian honours, the [[Bharat Ratna]] and [[Légion d'honneur|Legion of Honor]] respectively, and [[Mrinal Sen]], who is the recipient of the French distinction of Commander of the [[Ordre des Arts et des Lettres|Order of Arts and Letters]] and the Russian [[Order of Friendship]].

old_content: A number of homes are associated with O'Reilly, including his former main residence, Lissadell Tamura, with a beach in the private [[gated community]] [[Lyford Cay]]<ref name="Pittsburgh profile">Pittsburgh, 22 July 2001: Pittsburgh Post-Gazette, "Living large; Anthony O'Reilly rules a global business empire, enchants all those in his sphere and is now addressed as "Sir", Cristina Rouvalis</ref> near Nassau in the [[Bahamas]]. For many years his principal residence and later a major base, was [[Castlemartin House and Estate|Castlemartin]], a "big house" dating in current form from the 18th century, at [[Kilcullen]], [[County Kildare]] (which has associated stud farm and cattle breeding premises on the large estate lands). O'Reilly purchased Castlemartin in 1972 from the [[Grey Ruthven, 2nd Earl of Gowrie|Earl of Gowrie]], and spent millions on improvements to the house and on the restoration of the 15th century [[St. Mary's Church, Castlemartin|Church of St Mary]] in the grounds. On 15 February 2008 permission was granted for the development of two ancillary houses on a remote part of the estate, adjoining Kilcullen (Bridge) village's main street, incorporating residential, restaurant and retail space. In October 2007, O'Reilly paid a record €125,000 per acre for {{convert|60|acre|m2|adj=on}} Hollyhill Stud in Carnalway near Brannockstown,<ref>Leinster Leader, 17 October 2007: Auction Watch</ref> under 3 kilometres from Kilcullen. The stud farm on the banks of the Liffey, with a 10-room house and a cottage, was thought to have been intended for one of his daughters.<ref>The Irish Times, 11 October 2007, Property: Sales Results</ref>

old_content: '''Catherine II''', also '''Catherine of Valois''' or '''Catherine of Taranto''' (before 15 April 1303 – October 1346), was the recognised [[Latin Empire|Latin Empress of Constantinople]] from 1307–1346, although she lived in exile and only had authority over [[Frankokratia|Crusader States in Greece]].She was Queen consort of [[Kingdom of Albania (medieval)|Albania]]. As well as Princess consort of [[Achaea]] and Taranto, and also regent of Achaea from 1332–1341, and Governor of [[Kefalonia|Cephalonia]] from 1341–1346.
new_content: '''Catherine II''', also '''Catherine of Valois''' or '''Catherine of Taranto''' (before 15 April 1303 – October 1346), was the recognised [[Latin Empire|Latin Empress of Constantinople]] from 1307–1346, although she lived in exile and only had authority over [[Frankokratia|Crusader States in Greece]]. She was Queen consort of [[Kingdom of Albania (medieval)|Albania]]. As well as Princess consort of [[Achaea]] and Taranto, and also regent of Achaea from 1332–1341, and Governor of [[Kefalonia|Cephalonia]] from 1341–1346.

old_content: Estimates of Pando's age have also been influenced by changes in the understanding of establishment of aspen clones in western North America. Earlier sources argued germination and successful establishment of aspen on new sites was rare in the last 10,000 years and therefore, Pando's root system was likely over 10,000 years old.<ref name="MittonGrant1996" /> More recent observations, however, have shown seedling establishment of new aspen clones is a regular occurrence and can be abundant on sites exposed by [[wildfire]].<ref>{{cite journal|last=Kay |first= Charles E. |date=1993 |title=Aspen seedlings in recently burned areas of Grand Teton and Yellowstone National Parks |journal=Northwest Science |volume=67 |issue=2 |pages = 94–104 |url = https://research.libraries.wsu.edu/xmlui/bitstream/handle/2376/1576/v67%20p94%20Kay.PDF?sequence=1 }}</ref> These findings are summarized in the U.S. Forest Service's ''Fire Effects Information System'':<ref name="feis">{{cite web |last1=Howard |first1=Janet L. |title=''Populus tremuloides'' |url=http://www.fs.fed.us/database/feis/plants/tree/poptre/all.html#BOTANICAL%20AND%20ECOLOGICAL%20CHARACTERISTICS|website=Fire Effects Information System |publisher=U.S. Department of Agriculture, Forest Service, Rocky Mountain Research Station, Fire Sciences Laboratory |access-date=2018-11-17 |date=1996}}</ref>

old_content: '''William Howard Adams''' (October 10, 1946 – July 5, 2023)is an author, curator and lecturer on history and garden design. He is a senior fellow at the [[Dumbarton Oaks|Dumbarton Oaks Research Library]] in Washington, D.C. and a Fellow of the International Center for Jefferson Studies. His house, [[Hazelfield]], in [[Shenandoah Junction, West Virginia]] is listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]].
new_content: '''William Howard Adams''' (1926 – July 5, 2023)is an author, curator and lecturer on history and garden design. He is a senior fellow at the [[Dumbarton Oaks|Dumbarton Oaks Research Library]] in Washington, D.C. and a Fellow of the International Center for Jefferson Studies. His house, [[Hazelfield]], in [[Shenandoah Junction, West Virginia]] is listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]].

old_content: '''Imogen Gay Poots''' (born June 1989) is an English actress. She played Tammy in the post-apocalyptic horror film ''[[28 Weeks Later]]'' (2007), [[Linda Keith]] in the [[Jimi Hendrix]] biopic ''[[Jimi: All Is by My Side]]'' (2013), Debbie Raymond in the [[Paul Raymond (publisher)|Paul Raymond]] biopic ''[[The Look of Love (film)|The Look of Love]]'' (2013), and Julia Maddon in the American action film ''[[Need for Speed (film)|Need for Speed]]'' (2014). Also in 2014, she portrayed Jesse Crichton in ''[[A Long Way Down (film)|A Long Way Down]]'', alongside [[Pierce Brosnan]] and [[Aaron Paul]] and Izzie in Peter Bogdanovich's ''[[She's Funny That Way (film)|She's Funny That Way]]''. In 2016, she starred as Kelly Ann in the [[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]] series ''[[Roadies (TV series)|Roadies]]''. In 2019, she played Gemma in the sci-fi film ''[[Vivarium (film)]]''.  In 2020, she played Laura in ''[[The Father (2020 film)|The Father]]'' (2020). In 2022, she began playing the role of the mysterious Autumn in the [[Prime Video]] science fiction [[neo-Western]] series ''[[Outer Range]]''.

old_content: The cockpit crew consisted of [[Pilot in command|Captain]] Jesus Calderón Gaztelu (age 53), [[First officer (aviation)|First Officer]] Alfredo Perez Vega (54), [[Flight engineer|Flight Engineer]] Celedonio Martin Santos (42), and [[Radio operator|Radio Operator]]/[[Navigator#In aviation|Navigator]] Candido Garcia Bueno (51). Captain Calderón had 21,705 flight hours. First Officer Perez had 34,189 hours, Flight Engineer Martin had 15,317 hours of flight time, and Radio Operator/Navigator Garcia had 14,562 hours.
new_content: The cockpit crew consisted of [[Pilot in command|Captain]] Jesus Calderón Gaztelu (age 53), [[First officer (aviation)|First Officer]] Alfredo Perez Vega (54), [[Flight engineer|Flight Engineer]] Celedonio Martin Santos (42), and [[Radio operator|Radio Operator]]/[[Navigator#In aviation|Navigator]] Candido Garcia Bueno (51). Captain Calderón was hired in 1953 and had 21,705 flight hours, including 426 hours in the DC-10. First Officer Perez was hired in 1946 and had 34,189 hours, including 403 hours in the DC-10. Flight Engineer Martin was hired in 1952 and had 15,317 hours of flight time, including 263 hours in the DC-10. Radio Operator/Navigator Garcia was hired in 1941 and had 14,562 hours, including 384 hours in the DC-10.<ref name="AAR7414 final report"/>

old_content: Mwedihanga began his soccer career playing for Teenagers Football club in [[Ongwediva]].  He then moved to [[United Africa Tigers]], where he made a name for himself as a no nonsense centre back. In 2012, he joined [[AmaZulu F.C.|Amazulu FC]]. old_content: '''Gretchen Stoughton Anthony''' (January 8, 1969 – March 21, 2020) was an American woman from [[Jupiter, Florida]] who was murdered by her estranged husband, '''David Ethan Anthony''', in the early morning hours of March 21, 2020. David Anthony had attempted to persuade Gretchen Anthony to travel with him to [[Costa Rica]], where he believed they could escape the [[COVID-19 pandemic]]. When Gretchen declined, David entered her house in [[Abacoa, Florida]] and stabbed her to death in her garage. He then discarded her body in a nearby wooded area before fleeing the state.
new_content: '''Gretchen Stoughton Anthony''' (January 8, 1969 – March 21, 2020) was an American woman from [[Jupiter, Florida]], who was murdered by her estranged husband, '''David Ethan Anthony''', in the early morning hours of March 21, 2020. David Anthony had attempted to persuade Gretchen Anthony to travel with him to [[Costa Rica]], where he believed they could escape the [[COVID-19 pandemic]]. When Gretchen declined, David entered her house in [[Abacoa, Florida]], and stabbed her to death in her garage. He then discarded her body in a nearby wooded area before fleeing the state.

old_content: During the [[War of 1812]], Stewart commanded, successively, {{USS|Argus|1803|6}}, {{USS|Hornet|1805|6}}, and {{USS|Constellation|1797|6}}. Since ''Constellation'' was closely blockaded in Norfolk by the British, he took command of ''Constitution'' ("Old Ironsides") at [[Boston, Massachusetts|Boston]] on 18 July 1813.<ref name=":0" /> He conducted a successful sea raiding campaign hunting British vessels.
new_content: During the [[War of 1812]], Stewart commanded, successively, {{USS|Argus|1803|6}}, {{USS|Hornet|1805|6}}, and {{USS|Constellation|1797|6}}. Since ''Constellation'' was closely blockaded in Norfolk by the British, he took command of ''Constitution'' ("Old Ironsides") at [[Boston, Massachusetts|Boston]] on 18 July 1813.<ref name=":0" /> He made two brilliant cruises in her between 1813 and 1815.

old_content: Neo-plasticism assumes that when the painter tries to shape reality (or truth), he never does this from what he sees (object, matter, the physical), but from what originates within himself (subject, idea, the spiritual),<ref>Theo van Doesburg. ''The New Movement in Painting.'' Delft: J. Waltman, 1917. See [http://sdrc.lib.uiowa.edu/dada/De_Nieuwe_Beweging/pages/000cover.htm Digital Dada Library].</ref > or as [[Georges Vantongerloo]] puts it: "''La grande vérité, ou la vérité absolu, se rend visible à notre esprit par l'invisible''".<ref>Georges Vantongerloo, 'Réflexions', ''De Stijl'' , 1st volume, number 9 (July 1918): p. 100.</ref> Mondriaan calls this process 'internalization'.<ref name="mondrian" /> In addition, no painting is created by chance. Each painting is an interplay of space, plane, line and color. These are the ''visual (plastic) means in painting''. If the artist wants to approach the truth as closely as possible, he dissolves the natural form into these most elementary visual means. In this way the painter achieves universal harmony. The role of the [[artist]] (the individual or the subjective) is limited to determining the relationship between these visual means (the composition). The artist thus becomes a mediator between the spectator and the absolute (the objective).<ref>Theo van Doesburg. 'Fragments. I', ''De Stijl'', 1st volume, number 4 (February 1918): p. 47-48. See [http://sdrc.lib.uiowa.edu/dada/De_Stijl/001/004/pages/047.htm Digital Dada Library].</ref> Following Schoenmaekers - who combined the physical with the horizontal, and the spiritual with the vertical - these neo-plastic painters exclusively applied horizontal and vertical lines with rectangular areas of color.<ref>Friedman (1982; ISBN 9029080523): p. 111.</ref> The purpose of which was the radical simplification of painting in order to purify art of those elements that are not directly related to painting.

See [http://sdrc.lib.uiowa.edu/dada/De_Nieuwe_Beweging/pages/000cover.htm Digital Dada Library].</ref > or as [[Georges Vantongerloo]] puts it: "''La grande vérité, ou la vérité absolu, se rend visible à notre esprit par l'invisible''".<ref>Georges Vantongerloo, 'Réflexions', ''De Stijl'' , 1st volume, number 9 (July 1918): p. 100.</ref> Mondriaan calls this process 'internalization'.<ref name="mondrian" /> In addition, no painting is created by chance. Each painting is an interplay of space, plane, line and color. These are the ''visual (plastic) means in painting''. If the artist wants to approach the truth as closely as possible, he dissolves the natural form into these most elementary visual means. In this way the painter achieves universal harmony. The role of the [[artist]] (the individual or the subjective) is limited to determining the relationship between these visual means (the composition). The artist thus becomes a mediator between the spectator and the absolute (the objective).<ref>Theo van Doesburg. 'Fragments. I', ''De Stijl'', 1st volume, number 4 (February 1918): p. 47-48. See [http://sdrc.lib.uiowa.edu/dada/De_Stijl/001/004/pages/047.htm Digital Dada Library].</ref> Following Schoenmaekers - who associated the physical with the horizontal, and the spiritual with the vertical - the neo-plastic painters applied horizontal and vertical lines with rectangular areas of color in order to radically simplify painting, purifying art of those elements that are not directly related to expressing "pure reality". <ref>Friedman (1982; ISBN 9029080523): p. 111.</ref>

old_content: The name of the city of Osh derives from the river [[Vakhsh (river)|Vakhsh]], anthropomorphised there as a water goddess of the same name, who was worshipped (in tandem with Atash, the sacred fire) in a Zoroastrian shrine or fire temple situated in the Eagle Cave of the ancient sacred mountain [[Sulayman Mountain|Sulaiman-Too]]. The river Vakhsh itself, known also as Surkhob  or Kyzyl-Suu ( Turkic: “red water”) is a tributary of the Amu Darya, the course of the Vakhsh lying to the South of the Fergana valley, rising as it does near the village of [[Sary-Tash]] and flowing southwest to join the Amu Darya not far from [[Panj]].<ref>A little history of the city of Osh https://osh-hospital.narod.ru/history_osh.htm; Live the East. info@centralasia-travel.com; Retrieved 17/4/2024.</ref>

The river Vakhsh itself, known also as Surkhob  or Kyzyl-Suu ( Turkic: “red water”) is a tributary of the Amu Darya, the course of the Vakhsh lying to the South of the Fergana valley, rising as it does near the village of [[Sary-Tash]] and flowing southwest to join the Amu Darya not far from [[Panj]].<ref>A little history of the city of Osh https://osh-hospital.narod.ru/history_osh.htm; Live the East. info@centralasia-travel.com; Retrieved 17/4/2024.</ref>

old_content: Shakespeare's early classical and Italianate comedies, containing tight double plots and precise comic sequences, give way in the mid-1590s to the romantic atmosphere of his most acclaimed comedies.{{sfn|Ackroyd|2006|p=235}} ''[[A Midsummer Night's Dream]]'' is a witty mixture of romance, fairy magic, and comic lowlife scenes.{{sfn|Wood|2003|pp=161–162}} Shakespeare's next comedy, the equally romantic ''[[The Merchant of Venice|Merchant of Venice]]'', contains a portrayal of the vengeful Jewish moneylender [[Shylock]], which reflects dominant Elizabethan views but may appear derogatory to modern audiences.{{sfn|Wood|2003|pp=205–206}}{{sfn|Honan|1998|p=258}} The wit and wordplay of ''[[Much Ado About Nothing]]'',{{sfn|Ackroyd|2006|p=359}} the charming rural setting of ''[[As You Like It]]'', and the lively merrymaking of ''[[Twelfth Night]]'' complete Shakespeare's sequence of great comedies.{{sfn|Ackroyd|2006|pp=362–383}} After the lyrical ''[[Richard II (play)|Richard II]]'', written almost entirely in verse, Shakespeare introduced prose comedy into the histories of the late 1590s, ''[[Henry IV, Part 1|Henry IV, Part 1]]'' and ''[[Henry IV, Part 2|2]]'', and ''[[Henry V (play)|Henry V]]''. ''Henry IV'' features [[Falstaff]], rogue, wit and friennd of Prince Hal. His characters become more complex and tender as he switches deftly between comic and serious scenes, prose and poetry, and achieves the narrative variety of his mature work.{{sfn|Shapiro|2005|p=150}}{{sfn|Gibbons|1993|p=1}}{{sfn|Ackroyd|2006|p=356}} This period begins and ends with two tragedies: ''[[Romeo and Juliet]]'', the famous romantic tragedy of sexually charged adolescence, love, and death;{{sfn|Wood|2003|p=161}}{{sfn|Honan|1998|p=206}} and ''[[Julius Caesar (play)|Julius Caesar]]''—based on Sir [[Thomas North]]'s 1579 translation of [[Plutarch]]'s ''[[Parallel Lives]]''—which introduced a new kind of drama.{{sfn|Ackroyd|2006|pp=353, 358}}{{sfn|Shapiro|2005|pp=151–153}} According to Shakespearean scholar [[James S. Shapiro|James Shapiro]], in ''Julius Caesar'', "the various strands of politics, character, inwardness, contemporary events, even Shakespeare's own reflections on the act of writing, began to infuse each other".{{sfn|Shapiro|2005|p=151}}

''Henry IV'' features [[Falstaff]], rogue, wit and friennd of Prince Hal. Shapiro|James Shapiro]], in ''Julius Caesar'', "the various strands of politics, character, inwardness, contemporary events, even Shakespeare's own reflections on the act of writing, began to infuse each other".{{sfn|Shapiro|2005|p=151}}

old_content: The '''death camas miner bee''' or '''death camas bee''' (''Andrena astragali''), is a species of [[mining bee|miner bee]] in the family [[Andrenidae]]. It is found in North America. It specializes in feeding on the highly poisonous ''[[Toxicoscordion venenosum]]'', the meadow deathcamas, and close relatives. It is quite likely the only bee that can tolerate the deathcamas toxin, [[zygacine]].

old_content: The '''National Committee of Referees''' ([[Spanish language|Spanish]]: Comité National de Árbitros), also known as '''Technical Committee of Referees''', directly attends to the functioning of the federative collective of referees and is responsible, under subordination to the president of the RFEF, for the government, representation, and administration of the functions attributed to them.<ref name=Tech>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120308021000/http://www.rfef.es/index.jsp?nodo=25 |title=Comité Técnico de Árbitros |trans-title=Technical Committee of Referees |language=es |website=web.archive.org |access-date=24 March 2024 }}</ref> It is in charge of the operation and organization of the Spanish arbitration world. Of course, it is the body in charge of appointing matches or promotions of referees, assistant referees, match delegates, and football and futsal reporters in national categories.<ref name=Tech/> Likewise, it is the body in charge of communicating to FIFA the selection of international referees and assistants each season.

In 2011 the Minneapolis Park and Recreation Board (MPRB) visited the issue. Their legal counsel concluded that the board could not legally change the name, as state law gives that power to the Commissioner of Natural Resources, and then only in the first 40 years after the name was designated. Following the [[Charleston church shooting]] in June 2015, a fresh drive to change the name started via an online petition and the Park Board indicated it would look into whether they could change the lake's name through state action.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Brandt|first1=Steve|title=Lake Calhoun name change gets another look in Minneapolis|url=http://www.startribune.com/lake-calhoun-name-change-gets-another-look-in-minneapolis/309249161/|work=Star Tribune|date=June 23, 2015|access-date=June 25, 2015|archive-date=June 25, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150625211405/http://www.startribune.com/lake-calhoun-name-change-gets-another-look-in-minneapolis/309249161/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Brandt|first1=Steve|title=Minneapolis Park Board gives fresh look at renaming Lake Calhoun after South Carolina shootings|url=http://www.startribune.com/minneapolis-park-board-gives-fresh-look-at-renaming-lake-calhoun-after-south-carolina-shootings/309393471/|work=Star Tribune|date=June 24, 2015|access-date=June 25, 2015|archive-date=June 25, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150625012613/http://www.startribune.com/minneapolis-park-board-gives-fresh-look-at-renaming-lake-calhoun-after-south-carolina-shootings/309393471/|url-status=live}}</ref> At the time, the ''[[Minneapolis Star Tribune]]'' published an article quoting Calhoun's views on the black race:

old_content: Iran is a major [[Regional power|regional]] and [[middle power]], due to its large reserves of [[fossil fuel]]s, including the world's second largest [[Natural gas reserves in Iran|natural gas supply]], [[List of countries by proven oil reserves|third largest proven oil reserves]], its geopolitically significant location, its military capabilities, its regional influence, and its role as the world's focal point of [[Shia Islam]]. The [[Economy of Iran|Iranian economy]] is the world's [[List of countries by GDP (PPP)|19th-largest by PPP]]. It possesses the world's 14th strongest [[Islamic Republic of Iran Armed Forces|military]]. Iran is an active and founding member of the [[United Nations]], the [[Non-Aligned Movement|NAM]], the [[Economic Cooperation Organization|ECO]], the [[Organisation of Islamic Cooperation|OIC]] and the [[OPEC]]. It is a full member of both the [[Shanghai Cooperation Organisation]] and [[BRICS]]. Owing it to its long history and rich cultural legacy, Iran is home to 27 [[List of World Heritage Sites in Iran|UNESCO World Heritage Sites]], the 10th highest number in the world, and ranks 5th globally in the number of inscriptions of [[Intangible cultural heritage|Intangible Cultural Heritage]], or human treasures. Iran was the world's third fastest-growing tourism destination in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Goldstein |first=Michael |title=World Tourism Up 4%, Fastest-Growing Countries Include Iran, Myanmar |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/michaelgoldstein/2020/02/04/world-tourism-up-4-fastest-growing-countries-include-iran-myanmar/ |access-date=2024-05-03 |website=Forbes |language=en}}</ref>
